INSERT INTO `reviews` VALUES (21,232,'ST0P_TV','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104153065942542128076/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNeIj9I49IpXYWnbv9m5VRV_-fl4-aBkNv48uiOlTha5zK9kTSvA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'On our visit to Singapore, the zoo was high on our list and it absolutely delivered. The animal enclosures are exceptionally clean, spacious, and thoughtfully designed. While one can always debate whether wild animals should be kept in zoos, it’s clear that the Singapore Zoo makes animal wellbeing a priority. The animals looked healthy and relaxed, with no signs of unusual behaviour.\n\nFrom a photographer’s perspective, the layout is a real highlight. Many sections feature glass viewing panels, but there are also plenty of open areas that allow you to capture great shots without reflections. The monkey habitats deserve special mention: they offer generous space and allow the animals to move freely, creating natural and dynamic photography opportunities. As you explore the park, you may even encounter wild long-tailed macaques along the pathways.\n\nWe spent the entire day here and found it to be just the right amount of time to enjoy all the different zones. Unsurprisingly, we left with a full camera roll. Another plus: the zoo is very accessible by public transport, taking roughly 45–60 minutes depending on where you’re staying near the bay.\n\nThe entrance fee of 49 SGD (about 32.50€) is, in our view, absolutely worth it. High-quality care and maintenance require significant resources, and it’s clear that the zoo reinvests in providing a clean, enriching environment for both animals and visitors.','2025-12-01 09:58:54','Google','2025-12-15 17:54:21'),(22,232,'Lucy McGown','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105852373876911193026/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLR3yexrMYvrhSflntFJOytRiwo6sHngqfLUlYHjnI0I9NqFQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Animals were all well looked after, lots of staff cleaning and maintaining enclosures. There was a buggy you could jump on to go to different parts of the zoo. I did a circuit first to get the layout of the zoo and plan which animals I would visit. Lots of free roaming little critters that you could get up close to and get good photos of. The food was expensive but tasty.','2025-11-25 07:21:23','Google','2025-12-15 17:54:21'),(23,232,'Hareesh','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103832626118367617747/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKa7asaDB9wNevdN8E-aoc21lK-klR1LSyc54aBZJi3IDt0ll8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',4,'Great spot for kids. Just avoid visiting around the feeding times at 11 a.m. and 2 p.m.—most animals are passed out by then. Nice variety of species and overall a solid pick for a family day out.','2025-12-03 05:07:31','Google','2025-12-15 17:54:21'),(24,232,'Mohammad Sarosh','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116459213392781471684/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLxb7fXpuiOymzUuh1XRhvPtxjX7mmWufb40Gqigwwjw0PLo0zvQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',4,'Visited the zoo on a weekday afternoon and there was no rush. It\'s a really well maintained zoo and there\'s a zone for kids as well which is really thoughtfully made. The range of animals itself is not the greatest and it can take upwards of 3-4 hours to see all of them. The tram is very convenient to hop from one zone to the other. All in all, a great place to visit with kids but could use more birds and animals.','2025-11-04 14:28:18','Google','2025-12-15 17:54:21'),(25,232,'Annie B','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104505566220024505829/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXP5F5SjaHPW43clI_rfuq4C9p1aFUNwOHJI7_5pH5Z5vjvfEPU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Visiting Mandai Safari Singapore was an unforgettable experience. We bought tickets for all four attractions, and it turned out to be great value—definitely cheaper than purchasing them individually. Each park is huge, and with every attraction taking around 2–3 hours, it’s worth arriving as early as possible to make the most of the day.\n\nThe undeniable highlight for us was the Night Safari. It was truly out of this world—a completely unique way to experience wildlife. The atmosphere, the lighting, and the close-up encounters made it unlike any other zoo experience we’ve had.\n\nA big shout-out to Lilly, a zoo staff member who was incredibly helpful and friendly. She guided us around and made our visit even more enjoyable.\n\nIf you’re planning a trip to Singapore, I’d highly recommend adding Mandai Safari to your itinerary. The Night Safari alone makes it worth the visit, and overall it’s easily one of the best wildlife parks in the world.','2025-11-25 10:41:38','Google','2025-12-15 17:54:21'),(26,233,'Antonio On The Map','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110482098956095580342/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxltAvx0HrMGms7ogTFzGUb44iQWY8CNx3X_keszsAjkkdywuUnQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ 5/5 – The Best View in Singapore!\nThe SkyPark Observation Deck is an absolute must when visiting Singapore! Standing at the top of Marina Bay Sands gives you a breathtaking 360° view of the city — from the skyline and Gardens by the Bay to the ships in the harbor, it’s truly spectacular, especially at sunset or during the evening when the city lights start to glow.\n\nIt’s the perfect spot for photos and to really appreciate how modern and beautiful Singapore is. The staff are friendly, and everything feels well organized. Even if you’re not staying at the hotel, it’s 100% worth visiting for the experience.\n\nTip: go around 6–7 PM so you can enjoy both the daylight and nighttime views — and don’t forget to stay for the light show below! 🌇✨','2025-10-23 21:00:13','Google','2025-12-15 17:56:14'),(27,233,'dhruvi vora','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109490881837418575300/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKLNHuUnfxxL8ol2cQXHjZUyuZTZeQwlisxzqPOS7F_FNNfrhUc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Visited the Marina Bay Deck View  absolutely breathtaking!  The skyline, waterfront reflections, and breeze make it one of the most stunning viewpoints in Singapore. Perfect spot to catch the Marina Bay Sands light & water show at night and soak in the city lights. Peaceful, romantic, and picture-perfect a must-visit for every traveler!\n\nVisit during sunset hours, it\'s breathtaking to view entire singapore from above.\n\nOr else reserve your spot at LA vie restaurant at Marina Bay .\nDue to rains, we were to unable to view the deck therefore they reschedule our booking that\'s so sweet of them. On a clear day, one can see Malaysia and it\'s islands.','2025-11-08 05:56:34','Google','2025-12-15 17:56:14'),(28,233,'Paul Ciprian','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111291653184300497175/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSOLpK-3sNXhEO1aKgD4iJrFC72FanS0VTlOp0wsjGXHO_Wzn7=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8',3,'The view is extremely beautiful, both during the day and after dark. However, I didn\'t like how the flow of visitors was managed. There were a lot of people sitting on the ground along the railing, with their noses in their phones, uninterested in the scenery. They only obstructed the optimal view of those who wanted to get closer to the edge to admire the scenery and take a few pictures. I don\'t think lying on the floor should be allowed.\nThere is a small kiosk where you can buy something to drink. Unfortunately, cocktails are served in cheap plastic glasses.','2025-11-23 11:16:33','Google','2025-12-15 17:56:14'),(29,233,'Neha','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113254824026540268452/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrKDUIKHF8HE4ae0UkmhBeYfscy3KfEHVmeGSNUlLisRNMV9wE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Perched 56 stories above the heart of Singapore, the SkyPark Observation Deck is more than just a viewing platform; it is an architectural marvel that sits atop the three towers of the Marina Bay Sands hotel. ​Stepping onto the cantilevered deck, you are immediately hit by the scale of the city. The sheer height offers a bird\'s-eye perspective that makes the skyscrapers of the Central Business District look like Lego blocks.\nSunset in the Sky: The \"Golden Hour\" (around 6:45 PM – 7:15 PM) is the most coveted time to visit. Watching the sun dip below the horizon while the city lights flicker on is magical.\n​Spectra Light & Water Show: You can watch the famous light show happening at the Event Plaza below from a unique aerial perspective (usually at 8 PM and 9 PM), though you won\'t hear the music from up there.\n​A Taste Above: A small kiosk on the deck serving light bites, gelato, and beverages (including Singapore Slings) if you want a drink without sitting in a full restaurant\nThe Observation Deck shares the rooftop with several high-end venues.\n​CÉ LA VI: A club lounge and restaurant.\n​LAVO: An Italian restaurant and rooftop bar.\nWhether you are an architecture buff, a photographer, or just someone who loves a good view, the SkyPark Observation Deck delivers the definitive image of Singapore. It is pricey, but the memory of the wind in your hair as you look down at the Supertrees is priceless #SkyPark #Observation #Deck','2025-11-22 09:57:09','Google','2025-12-15 17:56:14'),(30,233,'Luciano Bianchi','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110679775359164739650/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtcTouUbZDYovN0-_QoRLQLSbyWpvPJx_-BRtB_BXQKpI30emPUw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',4,'An absolutely amazing experience!\nWe arrived around 6:30 PM to catch both the daytime and nighttime views, and it was completely worth it. Watching the sunset over Singapore’s skyline and then seeing the city light up at night was truly magical. The view from the top is breathtaking, offering a full panorama that perfectly captures the beauty of the city.\n\nThe best part is that there’s no time limit, so you can take your time enjoying the scenery and taking photos at your own pace.\n\nHowever, it can get very crowded, and you often have to find and « get » your own spot to take pictures, which makes the experience feel a bit disorganized. There is a lot of person that will push you a bit around or try to take your spot.\n\nStill, it’s an unmissable experience and one of the best viewpoints in Singapore. 🌇📸','2025-10-20 05:49:31','Google','2025-12-15 17:56:14'),(31,234,'ChicLifeByte','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101714563826076303803/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_GRVld2TmvWT16LcXCZSFTq3L6oWAFmviDVNVSLoXmFW8CtoA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'If there’s one activity in Singapore that perfectly balances fun, views, and a little bit of thrill - it’s the Skyline Luge and Skyride at Sentosa.\n\nI finally got to experience it on my recent Singapore trip, and it was honestly such a highlight! From gearing up for the Luge to gliding down the different tracks, everything felt exciting but still so easy and enjoyable. We chose the 3-ride pass, and I’d totally recommend it - each track has its own twists and corners, so every ride feels fresh and a little different. By the third round, you’re already more confident and wishing for one more go.\n\nAfter that, the Skyride was the calmest, most beautiful transition. Floating above Sentosa with that cool breeze, taking in the greenery and the coastline… it felt like the perfect way to slow things down. The best part? It’s great for all ages - even my mom joined in and had such a lovely time!\n\nWhether you’re travelling with friends, family, or even on a solo trip, this combo is one experience you shouldn’t miss. The views, the vibe, the whole atmosphere - it’s all worth it.\n\nIf Sentosa is on your itinerary, make sure this is too.','2025-11-24 17:17:40','Google','2025-12-15 17:58:17'),(32,234,'Franco Migliorati','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100371330244756270290/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkZnEeD-A71-8sTYTmOmEFkth5fm4r4G3NJjaT8fP8fl_T-hUoqw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'unmissable experience at Sentosa Island. Great fun and very well organised. The pack for 4 tracks is great value for money, 36 SDG. The skyride to take you back is worth it. The left one doesn\'t go as high as the right one. Great day out with friends or family.','2025-11-24 22:42:45','Google','2025-12-15 17:58:17'),(33,234,'Denis González Navas','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116926906689270181527/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCUnma2cQmBd6MOfN1en6gc6V7N6iF3bV2aucV01gjsSmNgr9S=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'I would definitely recommend this activity to anyone on Sentosa. Although I felt the circuits are kind of short because they are 600m long(maybe consider taking 3 rides +), this is by far a very enjoyable experience.\n\nNote: I’m 1.85 and weigh about 350 pounds and I was able to fit well on the luge.\n\nPlease note that if you’re buying tickets in advance, only the ones bought on the official website will provide an expedite access.','2025-11-30 18:49:52','Google','2025-12-15 17:58:17'),(34,234,'Vincent Ibarreta','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104385105359455953774/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXWuCXaBCT31S_TlBOhNJYs1FE63IpHivuSEOQG_Vb25zxWD00_=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',4,'Its my first time spending so much for a ride. I wanted yo try something new and I went with it. The experience was really fun, however the limit to having 3 rides only for the price was a bit too much.\n\nThe ride going up with the cable was fun, I suggest going for the 7:00pm ride, so you can still have some light before the sunset.\n\nYou would also be able to see some of the cuty views from up there.\n\nWhat I suggest for it to have as an additional is atleast have a device that can record the pov or something like that.\n\nOverall, pretty good experience, would definitely try to find similar places like this.','2025-10-20 12:01:25','Google','2025-12-15 17:58:17'),(35,234,'Lynn Ong','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117186841384854455620/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLb_HpQN8MZWDl22h--14an2-MjrbE1jlTS35eWfPJ_niGAAw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'We had an absolute blast! The rides were so much fun that we ended up going on 5 of them - and we still didn\'t feel like we\'d had enough! The entire experience felt very safe & smooth. The staff were always around & they were super helpful & friendly. Highly recommend this fun activity for families!','2025-12-05 23:21:39','Google','2025-12-15 17:58:17'),(36,235,'W T','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107322582965282125818/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLx811TsEHPi39xS8XUMnmaFQ-lbA1MigyxVI6LKciMk5ohOw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'Went during weekday. Nobody except us and another family. There is a 10% discount for SAFRA. The staff were very friendly and absolutely helpful.\n\nI paid $80 for 1hr (+bumper car) for 2 adults and 1 child. It was absolutely worth it because for them to bring down a 36degrees climate to sub-zero temperature is an immense feat on its own. I don\'t think the entry price I paid was enough to pay for the electricity bill.\n\nIt is not a big place but we got the thrill which we sought - some snow fun, and sub-zero temperature. The bumper car was my daughter\'s favourite.\n\nThe downside is the phototaking policy. No phototaking and videotaking. I thought it was for safety but realised it was very safe within the premise.\n\nThe photographers took about 50 photos while we were inside. there were two options:\n•$88 for all the digital copies, or,\n•$100 for all the digital copies + snow globe and 2 printed photos.\n\nWhile it seems more valuable for the latter, if not for the milestone of my daughter\'s 3yo birthday, I wouldn\'t have bought it. It is simply overpriced drawing a comparison to those at USS or GardenByTheBay....','2025-09-26 03:39:13','Google','2025-12-15 18:00:48'),(37,235,'Hiang Ar','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101185220797498251612/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUA05b2dpLoNwt-jBfaQ_M3lhk3zmyIFiO4vtMThzlTzYvUGfcR=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',3,'The place feels quite run down and doesn’t seem to have been renovated for a long time. The snow slide is fun, but the tire’s hole is too big — your butt can drag on the floor during the slide, which makes it uncomfortable. The photo prices are also quite expensive: $50 for the soft copies and $60 for all soft copies plus one printed photo.','2025-11-09 05:09:46','Google','2025-12-15 18:00:48'),(38,235,'vinnie vi','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102966395326484135262/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjZ1A4UdHsrUUTOfJ0bmSyNjoLZnGcfjERNzpNUuG-ue4AWQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',2,'Only one picture shared. Because I saw \"do not take photo and video\" noticed board after I snapped this pic.\nThe place is quite small,only 1 ride game for adult.\nThe pictures cost very expensive one pic need sg35,if all soft copies and free 2 pics need 88 or 85, I not really remember the actual price but sure that is 80sgd above.','2025-10-12 01:56:05','Google','2025-12-15 18:00:48'),(39,235,'Goh Phoebe','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105025019280262870270/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVx30DbveKG8DZd_8dVwlvdy6TDU_0NjZ2NuhC8Sdg71TZJKvBZ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Bring lots of warm winter wear. Pro tip: heat packs also help warm the fingers\nJackets and shoes are provided. They close at 5pm!','2025-08-29 09:17:33','Google','2025-12-15 18:00:48'),(40,235,'archchayan manoharan','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112228472817786095951/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0gEE5loNrU5Qg438-oYlOcXVjZU0a0d743wPkTAZtLL7ehYUF=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',1,'⭐ 1/5 — Disappointing Experience, Not Worth the Price\n\nIt really feels like a scam for visitors. We bought the ticket package for $27, which included 1 hour of snow play and one ice bumper car ride. It seemed fair at first, but once inside, there were several hidden charges — $2 for a locker and $6.60 for gloves.\n\nThe photography part was the worst. There was no proper advice or notice about photo charges before entry. Staff took photos inside and only at checkout did we find out that you need to pay $50 to get 2 printed photos and unlimited soft copies. If we had known earlier, we could have posed and taken better pictures since personal phones aren’t allowed inside.\n\nAltogether, we ended up spending around $101, and honestly, the attractions were very limited. Not worth the time or money. The experience really needs more transparency, better communication, and fair pricing.','2025-10-18 12:16:12','Google','2025-12-15 18:00:48'),(41,236,'Rissa J','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115070270309213567607/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBt-1VBhdtaHta8A8lETOhWTRznCJi7XzvDlv4CM6OnWdiK_GM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',1,'The street games football area is unsafe for younger kids. Although there was a staff member manning the station, it was as good as having no one there. He looked like a temp just clocking hours, occasionally checking his phone or wandering off to chat with other staff.\n\nI saw older kids kicking the ball with so much force that it hit younger kids hard. The staff witnessed it but simply called out softly, “Are you okay?” The boy didn’t even hear him. He should have walked over and checked properly and made sure the child was alright. Younger kids often don’t know how to react when they’re hurt. At the very least, the staff should have reminded the older kids to be more considerate when playing with younger ones.\n\nMy son ended up being hit hard in the head by a ball kicked. When I asked about safety measures for mixed-age play, the staff shrugged and replied in a nonchalant tone, “Uh don’t have… this one all free play.”\n\nSpeechless.\n\nEven with waivers, proper supervision and basic safety guidelines should be in place. Without proper monitoring and clear safety measures, it’s only a matter of time before a serious accident happens.','2025-12-12 15:09:35','Google','2025-12-15 18:02:53'),(42,236,'Prajakta Patil','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112255900978295117164/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtlzK2AByFIND4vAoXRPScAXUVYcfqKLaMt4Y0jkW8HINgkvLA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'It was very fun filled experience. We took birthday package for my daughter\'s bday celebration. Herself and her friends enjoyed it a lot. Lot of activities with full of fun. Adults also liked it. Suggest to book weekdays as it was less queue and kids can repeat the activities. look forward to visit again.','2025-11-19 11:15:53','Google','2025-12-15 18:02:53'),(43,236,'Lavania Rogers','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114635954817599788856/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlNeBogBbnI5VVbenJ67M4EqN4cANdcR6zePQ0YoZFmLsbfYWNvw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'I have been to SuperPark many times but today was extra special with dear Ms Dalifah assisting us. I was a little flustered and she was so patient and explained to me on the costs and options. I took my time and she was so patient and so professional and caring towards my situation. I truly commend her for her absolutely fantastic customer service and to be honest it\'s very refreshing to meet such service superstars like Ms Dalifah! Please recognise her for her efforts and service excellence. 5 stars for SuperPark and 5 Stars for Ms Dalifah!','2025-11-26 11:02:54','Google','2025-12-15 18:02:53'),(44,236,'Tan LiShi','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116001849417268357934/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWf1JObRkEHXr47i7EWXCxcqs49FC-FcvRwm_FVRxCTLKMbu7fo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Our first but definitely not the last time here. The children had a blast! There were enough stations and activities to keep the children entertained for the whole day.','2025-08-18 15:03:10','Google','2025-12-15 18:02:53'),(45,236,'Ming Wei Teo','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116751374509970589589/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKyucAM0QflYkqZdWgrTwq788GccVzoj_WUUYc-sbOY-OR9tQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',2,'My first visit since Superpark underwent renovation. Previous visit was in Apr 2024. I was kinda shocked by how much smaller it has become especially the play area for kids under 100cm. I recall the original playground was easily 10x the current size and offered lots of variety and experiences for the younger kids. And there was strict control in granting access to kids of the acceptable height. However, today\'s visit was quite disappointing and chaotic. Older kids frequently visited the ball pit area which is the only play area for kids under 100cm. Although a staff member would sometimes dropped by and requested these kids to exit, it was clear the current control measure was insufficient. I would suggest parents with young kids should explore other more appropriate venues.','2025-08-31 09:49:07','Google','2025-12-15 18:02:53'),(46,237,'Benedict Correya','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113292377967743781974/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGGK89xGI0xzaALnRSueP9q_XEKHVc_VzRg-FwAWXsA37LqP5y7A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',5,'Universal Studios Singapore never loses its magic, no matter how many times we visit. My wife and I have been here several times, and every trip still feels exciting and memorable. The park is incredibly well-maintained, the staff are warm and energetic, and the whole place has this lively atmosphere that instantly puts you in a good mood.\n\nWe love starting our day early to enjoy our favourite attractions like Transformers, Revenge of the Mummy, and Jurassic Park Rapids Adventure with minimal waiting. Even after multiple visits, the thrill is still the same. The shows are also a highlight, especially WaterWorld, which continues to impress every single time.\n\nWhat makes USS truly special is how well everything is organised: clean surroundings, smooth operations, and plenty of places to relax, dine, and take photos. It’s the kind of place where you can have fun without feeling rushed. Each visit becomes a full day of joy, laughter, and moments we genuinely treasure.\n\nA fantastic destination for couples, families, and anyone looking to escape into a world of adventure. We’ll definitely keep coming back — it’s become one of our favourite places in Singapore.','2025-12-02 12:50:03','Google','2025-12-15 18:04:13'),(47,237,'Dave Wales','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103661813882008144238/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzkZtoy-9GeCiNajjNAFbvSaccydo_meHhmAbdwmpZupDAkHH9=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',3,'Universal Studios Singapore is visually impressive and well-organized, with themed zones that are fun to explore and friendly staff throughout the park. However, our experience was significantly impacted by the closure and disruption of several major attractions, which made the full ticket price hard to justify.\n\nUnfortunately, on the day of our visit, two of the park’s main headline attractions were completely closed: Revenge of the Mummy and the Battlestar Galactica: HUMAN vs. CYLON roller coasters. These rides are often considered must-dos and are a big reason many visitors choose Universal Studios Singapore in the first place. Their absence greatly reduced the overall thrill and excitement of the park.\n\nIn addition, WaterWorld, one of the most popular live shows, was also closed for the entire day. To make matters worse, the Steven Spielberg film set attraction was shut down in the middle of the show, leaving guests confused and disappointed.\n\nDespite these significant closures, full-price tickets were still charged, with no discount, partial refund, or alternative compensation offered. Paying the same price while being unable to access several of the park’s top attractions felt unfair, especially for visitors who may only come once.\n\nOn the positive side, the park is clean, family-friendly, and some rides and shows that were operating were still enjoyable. However, with so many key experiences unavailable, the visit felt incomplete.\n\nOverall, Universal Studios Singapore has great potential and can be an excellent theme park experience, but when multiple main attractions are closed, guests should be informed clearly in advance or offered price adjustments. For us, it was a good but disappointing visit, earning an overall 3 out of 5 stars.','2025-11-28 13:40:31','Google','2025-12-15 18:04:13'),(48,237,'Srinivas C','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102873722584518446253/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYBjyKIH5U9FYFjp0HcOS4KeWSLuTl_oKL89bcWLFJFRLsU9cD=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'An absolutely awesome place to visit! 🎢🎉\n\nUniversal Studios Singapore is one of the best theme parks I’ve been to — full of excitement, creativity, and fun for all ages. The park is very well-maintained, with different themed zones that make you feel like you’re walking through movie sets. From Hollywood Boulevard to Jurassic Park and Sci-Fi City, every corner has something special to explore.\n\nI highly recommend buying the Express Pass, especially if you’re visiting during weekends or holidays. It’s totally worth it to skip the long queues and enjoy more rides without waiting for hours.\n\nFor families with young kids, do note that children under 122 cm in height can’t join many of the big rides for safety reasons. However, there are still plenty of things for them to enjoy — character meet-and-greets, live shows, photo spots, and gentle rides that are perfect for little ones.\n\nThe food options inside the park are good, though a bit pricey (as expected in theme parks), but the experience overall makes up for it. Staff are friendly and helpful, and the atmosphere is energetic from start to finish.\n\nIf you’re in Singapore, this is definitely a must-visit attraction. Plan your day well, go early, and make the most of your visit — you’ll leave with amazing memories and probably a few new favorite movies! 🎬✨','2025-10-26 16:19:01','Google','2025-12-15 18:04:13'),(49,237,'Brian Z','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100433297684456277708/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUZx9C_ctnQH8_ga5QYIB-FFK4YBHiPUBgPJTfKJiBGEOwfZx5Gg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'The park isn’t very big, it has all the classic Universal elements. Characters from Shrek, Madagascar, and Despicable Me also come out for photos, which makes the visit even more fun.\n\nThere are plenty of food options inside. We tried pizza, fried shrimp, hot dogs, and the turkey leg, and everything tasted pretty good. The atmosphere is lively, and the rides are enjoyable for both adults and kids. Overall, the children had a great time, and it was a fun and easy day at the park.','2025-11-28 14:28:16','Google','2025-12-15 18:04:13'),(50,237,'J Chan','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104050587869976825442/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJ-0J9h8dp3fh0N1G3d2ucsRwe6sxKmIwEhIUGBGS-xuRNDg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'Went in the evening for the Halloween Horrors which is only available in October. The 4 haunted houses were amazingly scary! I love Stranger Things, so I was happy to see it as one of the haunted houses.\n\nThere were also actors outside with amazing makeup. There were also some shows available and some rides open during the visit from 7pm till midnight.\n\nI would advise to buy the tickets online in advance and go at 7pm. It was very crowded and the queue for each haunted house was almost an hour. You can buy express as top up to avoid queues but we opt not to.\n\nIt was also very warm but at least they sell cold drinks and have water fountains to top up your water bottle. Bring a portable fan and dress light if you have one!\n\nAll in all, I loved it. .Just be prepared for the crowd and heat