If you’re visiting Sentosa or Singapore, this is an absolute must-see attraction. Go a bit early to get a good seat and enjoy the cool sea breeze before the show starts. 🌅\n\nA truly memorable experience for families, couples, and tourists of all ages. Wings of Time proves that Singapore knows how to blend technology, art, and storytelling into pure magic. ✨🎇','2025-10-27 05:00:57','Google','2025-12-15 18:07:33'),(58,239,'Pankaj Kedia','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111522898328377061432/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4nUtuRqwzwIta_mSOjESUWpUrRq9KWAagaugMaEfz9lSrZMpe0w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'This is a very nice light and sound show and pure pice of art. The artist has really done a commendable job in preparing this show. More than the story I liked there art work. Much recommended if you visit Santos.','2025-11-01 02:05:57','Google','2025-12-15 18:07:33'),(59,239,'Aniket Pargaonkar','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107008629195316536929/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpThbQA1shNBrmuFxTm8vK4-5O4WkFOEz39vNMsbHTBBGxJYpiYg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'This show starts at 7:40 PM on the Sentosa Island every day. People tend to go and reserve seats in advance more than one hour before the start of the show. It’s a pretty nice show with laser and Music. You should plan to sit after the sixth of the seventh row from the front because there is a big chance of you getting wet otherwise.','2025-10-27 07:14:20','Google','2025-12-15 18:07:33'),(60,239,'Taking Guatengco','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100218519854276102105/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwereKCAD7xtoyN_4JgQmHqH7kl-EdLlkJiFmh4jb8659kV-oz=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'We’d highly recommend the Wings of Time show if you’re visiting Sentosa. On a weekday evening when it’s less crowded, the experience is super smooth and very enjoyable. And yes — for us the show did start earlier, just be there as early 15mins before the