'2025-11-15 21:46:06','Google','2025-12-15 18:27:04'),(122,252,'Black Cuban','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113634076371017272324/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBOHlL21-O2zG0XLQubxPsHA-yhGlCHrl1i9oMGsj63nf01neUmQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'A Natural Masterpiece – Truly the Eyes of God!\n\nAbsolutely breathtaking! Prohodna Cave is one of the most awe-inspiring natural wonders I\'ve ever visited. The two symmetrical openings in the ceiling — famously called the “Eyes of God” — create an atmosphere that’s both spiritual and surreal. When sunlight shines through, it feels like you\'re being watched by the heavens.\n\nThe cave itself is easy to access, with a short walk from the parking area, and there’s no entrance fee. You can walk through the whole cave in about 20–30 minutes, but take your time — it’s worth soaking in the view from all angles.\n\nBonus: if you\'re into adrenaline, there\'s bungee jumping from the large entrance (only on certain days). Rock climbers also use the area, but even for a casual visitor, this is a must-see.\n\nTip: Wear sturdy shoes — it can be a bit slippery, especially after rain.\n\nDefinitely one of Bulgaria’s hidden gems. Don\'t miss it if you\'re in the region!','2025-07-02 12:18:23','Google','2025-12-15 18:27:04'),(123,252,'Lyudmila Makarova','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108272288041607397357/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIp_GD2GYPOYXEbRpqx-xqtR_R10rNS9nIs6CmMUUeBWOaNr8D=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Amazing place! Visited Monday evening and there were just few people.  There is another entrance from the other side and locals use that entrance since there is no hiking required at all (not sure about the road quality though).   But we were the only ones who parked at Google spot. The climb is kind of steep at some places. Good shoes are the must!','2025-09-15 22:17:22','Google','2025-12-15 18:27:04'),(124,252,'Candace Tantilov','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102275152225450019006/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZCuWEb_o2NRHFItayPXrgpX-4rgwFkxDSfOq41ZInlhBclCpQFA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'An excellent location to immerse yourself in nature both in the cave and to hike further with views that are picturesque.  A must visit for tourists. We have been both early morning which was great to avoid large crowds anded the tour buses, but it was much colder and not favorable for the hike part. However, we have also been in summer and did a 3 hour scenic hike/walk in nature with the kids. It did mean however that the cave section was quite crowded so take that in mind. Both seasons were pretty.','2025-11-11 17:52:37','Google','2025-12-15 18:27:04'),(125,252,'Ivan Mour','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107722280345317422653/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_9zNtpoDRajQHcm6DUM5vdSb5qK1j5wbmtvSK8Y3jSUBkSv8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'A beautiful cave with high ceilings and open fresh air. Very good for people with claustrophobia,light and air are always abound. Small cave and easy to explore, a few parts of it are a bit slippery though so appropriate shoes would be advised. The highlight of the cave are the two eye-like holes in the ceiling that look like eyes,and hence the name “eyes of god” they have. Reaching the rear opening of the cave there are paths that lead downwards to the banks of a river and then theres another path that leads up the mountain,to a little monastery made of stone. Very dangerous path that one, proceed only with caution,if at all.','2025-09-15 20:32:30','Google','2025-12-15 18:27:04'),(126,253,'Uwe R. (Vielreisender)','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106707217497688524650/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKjKGl8NiRqEojcqCql2iZ1bMsZpEfzYVxlWRE5PNoQ9sYgQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Best place to bei. Spiritual and cultural Highlight placed in magical mountain scenery. Parking ahead with a few Meters walkway possible free of Charge. Highly recommend. If you avoid peaktime, than It ist more relaxing. Full around noon.','2025-11-09 14:53:47','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:03'),(127,253,'George Geo','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107677432858302941129/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZiFLCWe8ZAB5mTQRoYX2XUA70llmtmNSzHEcbhTIH4XzeJphy=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Magnificent and unforgettable!\nRila Monastery is truly one of Bulgaria’s greatest treasures. The architecture is stunning, surrounded by breathtaking mountain scenery, and the atmosphere is peaceful and spiritual. The frescoes and details inside are incredible — a must-visit for anyone traveling in Bulgaria. Absolutely worth the trip from Sofia!','2025-11-09 20:45:06','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:03'),(128,253,'Marta Capova','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112628691818789330426/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUottI2N3SroOvMiiIKihxbh5Ma9uV37D8xOzcR-P5cQ5GBGLT-yw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Beautiful Monastery and beautiful surrounding. The road from Rila to Monastery was magical as forest around this Autumn was like fairy tale.\nIt was on and off rain so not many tourists came (perfect!). You are not allowed to take photos inside the church and walk into the residential area.\nEntry is free (not sure about museum as I didn’t get in)','2025-10-25 23:33:38','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:03'),(129,253,'Ali Aghajafari','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118065713398441819980/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQGV-RhATu9ACOrwZE2hQOBZ4hdqrBq3I7i6q0GzD9mu0QGio=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Rila Monastery is truly breathtaking. Nestled in the mountains, it feels like stepping into a peaceful world far removed from everyday life. The architecture is stunning—colorful arches, intricate frescoes, and beautifully preserved details everywhere you look. The courtyard is especially magical, with the striped façade and central church creating a postcard-perfect view.\n\nInside the church, the frescoes are extraordinary and worth taking your time to appreciate. The surrounding nature is equally impressive; the fresh mountain air and quiet trails make the whole visit feel rejuvenating.\n\nParking and access are straightforward, and there are small shops nearby with local treats and souvenirs.\n\nA must-visit if you’re in Bulgaria—both for its history and its serene atmosphere.','2025-11-15 09:39:37','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:03'),(130,253,'Tibor','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112161006011370070852/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4OOWobe8XluLdExxIo6NECTMqOXhOwdhdHXRX6tNrGhxnyOHC2Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Rila Monastery is about a 1.5-hour drive from Sofia, nestled deep in the mountains. It’s best to go by car — the road is easy and takes you through stunning scenery. Plan to spend around two hours at the monastery itself, plus extra time to explore the surrounding area. The complex is breathtaking — beautifully preserved and full of history. Don’t miss the small museum and the icon exhibition next to it. From the courtyard, the colorful buildings set against the mountain backdrop are truly spectacular. Behind the monastery, you’ll also find a restaurant and a few souvenir shops.\nIt’s worth arriving early — I got there around 10 a.m., when it was still peaceful, but by 11:30 the tour buses start to arrive and it gets crowded.','2025-11-07 14:29:39','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:03'),(131,254,'Rob Hall','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115804774390050258959/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVf7BB0c1F1WU3-NwyyNfcVpPcAKqQvCczgF2XiRrmBRXSmBY5r=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',5,'Incredible hike and beautiful scenery! The hike is not at all difficult except for the initial climb up the ridge, then its mostly flat with a wonderful view of the mountains. The other path is slightly more scramble- best to come down this way as the view isn\'t as good anyway.\n\nFew things to note:\n\nThe chair lift is often closed in October for maintenance- you can find this information on their website. If its closed you might get lucky and have jeeps driving you up the path, more likely to be on a weekend. If you book directly through a hostel this will likely be possible.\n\nThe weather was incredible even in late October. The only snow was on the mountains themselves and not on the paths- although they were icy in places due to recent rain.\n\nThere is a cabin at the start selling coffee and refreshments, aswell as hot food and beer. Great place to start and finish your walk. There is also a few souvenirs at the bottom\n\nBrilliant experience, best to book through a hostel on a proper guide to make sure your prepared properly','2025-10-29 00:01:50','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:58'),(132,254,'Sherry M','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109668263761046823370/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNHV053LHUbgOR_UieFgpgRgb3xpJEmbYZ8S8zSYVlbdAwjW_HQg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Breathtaking views, amazing nature and great walk and energy. First time visiting and we were hypnotised by the beauty of Rila. Easy to follow the signs of the hike, we missed couple of the lakes, as the weather turned cloudy and rained and rushed us to get to dry place. I absolutely recommend visiting and taking a good time to stop and take in the views .','2025-08-27 07:14:08','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:58'),(133,254,'Stephanie Mihaylova','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110851027955507654866/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLds_DyZB43Y8CPxdgxUBYpYbzaHPwJsZq9jbMRhadfPD1r5pt=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'We decided to skip the lift from the hut and do the hike from the parking point - it was completely worth it. From start to finish, it took us about 4 hours to pass through all the lakes, with only one quick stop for food. The trail is well-marked.\n\nThe views are absolutely breathtaking, each lake is stunning. The trail is a bit challenging without the lift, but so worth it for the experience. Must-do if you’re in Bulgaria!\n\n* We started hiking at 6:30 AM and were so glad we did — the trail was peaceful, almost empty, and you could really enjoy the sounds of nature. People only started arriving when the lift opened around 8:30, so going early made a huge difference.','2025-08-17 09:25:22','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:58'),(134,254,'Алёна Виноградова','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116998469032400953931/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxoC-4s17Cogbd6LsiuvYpTMqOC0TlNEdru84pX_R0124Zi6kDlg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'very beautiful! I wouldn\'t call the route easy. You don\'t need special equipment, but frequent climbs up the mountain over rocks and descents are exhausting. Therefore, I advise you to leave as early as possible to make stops for rest. Children cope normally, but for older people it might be very difficult in some places. Be sure to take a hat and sunscreen, as there is no shade.\n\nWe saw 5 lakes out of 7. I think we\'ll come back another time and reach the end.','2025-07-22 19:32:40','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:58'),(135,254,'Adra Anderson','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112816628419642256706/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_1E7A5iHG_4aG4F_aYgcu1TCZSem8BFFe24US9_Dx_CMv0PRuFg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'I took the ski lift up, arrived at the hut at 11:15 on a Sunday in July. There were plenty of other people going up at this time. I was not bothered because the trail is wide and long for most of the way and you are too busy picking your jaw off the ground because you will be in awe of the magic and beauty of this place. Go up the lakes around the kidney lake (or just follow other people going to the right of the hut.). It\'s all as beautiful as the photos. Do take sunscreen and reapply. I wore proper hiking boots and saw many people wearing a variety of shoes that I would not deem suitable but they did anyways. I also advise sun protection for your body. I wore shorts and burned my legs. The too was windy and the last part is very steep, so you work up a sweat and then the wind hits you. You will feel cold. Take a long sleeved short or something for the top.  Go down the yellow path to get back to the ski lift. I found so many stunning Alpine flowers. There is also a hut with a restaurant looking at one the lakes on this side. It is a 5 mile or 8 km hike with a lot of elevation gain. I was able to do it in 3 hours and 45 minutes, not including skit lift time.','2025-07-14 21:01:20','Google','2025-12-15 18:28:58'),(136,255,'Vitor Bernardo','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109760465520736629116/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6zdf4ATm8i36QFKeeIePRuZBR2ZnGilJGNiKMLaZkQ2npaw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',1,'Avoid at all costs!!! Nothing to see here.\nStaff does not speak English and are even rude. You pay 8 lev for seeing a model (see picture) of the city and a fake model inside of a building (also in the photos). They try to offer a 3D visit for extra 10 lev.','2024-08-01 08:27:30','Google','2025-12-15 18:30:29'),(137,255,'Dimo Astadjov','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112018473613667176251/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZSSM6NB6WV0Qh_7wyoWPI3WdC1niyCw_CiYPbl-32UgZS1lY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'All-family attraction with essential knowledge about Bulgarian heritage.','2025-09-14 03:51:57','Google','2025-12-15 18:30:29'),(138,255,'ardreth','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102836105273695595546/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhb5aBww3ISO9VHyfcqFl_j0aeUz6uO8Vso7-QOcQ9_5tKgbo3=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',1,'A tourist trap whit a huge parking lot and a shiny exterior, but there is nothing actually archaeological inside, despite a nice reconstruction of a roman city. So no actual findings, no mound, just some (well made) reconstructions and for things like a fotoshot in historical costums and a VR-Video you have to pay extra... So avoid it completely and better go to the \"three mound parking lot\" next door, where you can see the mounds for real!','2025-05-25 05:46:27','Google','2025-12-15 18:30:29'),(139,255,'Asli Kusoglu','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104284195060069733757/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8PLr8waKMmYlxc9R29cIJQqg-vtydyG_KFh1HE1Nn_aGCA7D8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',1,'It is a tourist trap and everything is fake. Just 3D models. Shortly do not go there and spent your money. Go directly to the real tombs!','2025-07-05 09:46:10','Google','2025-12-15 18:30:29'),(140,255,'darksam644','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100103224249453907937/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBACbWwBt599-g6K994UMUUlq2elhCSQegCCsfGqjjX3KWt5USYQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',1,'Left after 10 minutes, complete waste of money. This place honestly baffles me. It\'s new & well maintained, money has definitely been invested in this place, but then there is just nothing interesting to see. A few models and statues, none of which are actually old. A 3D cinema and the opportunity to try on costumes, both of which are in addition to the entry fee, making the entry ticket a complete rip-off. If it was presented as \"Shipka 3D cinema experience\" I think it would be much more successful.','2024-09-29 08:20:09','Google','2025-12-15 18:30:29'),(141,256,'Linda Johnson','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112199855670808086912/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLB7v26rvht7cf6G2Hf7o3j1E52LjTlnaZ2JE4x9TC-8gw-ag=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Beautifully done interactive  aquarium.\nGreat for kids to learn and love nature.\nJust wish it had been made with wider aisles as prams are everywhere.\nLoved the sharks and stingrays but really it all was a joy.\nWe went on a Monday and it was busy but not impossible. I would think weekends could get hectic.','2025-11-25 22:32:46','Google','2025-12-15 18:32:04'),(142,256,'Alan Bryant','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101507959705048874618/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX03U_LHtgqoy3B-q5QYnPGE-TcLeSk9IYmOEWErrIIy02T9-rb=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Really loved this aquarium.  Easy to buy tickets online (and can save when bundling with collocated attractions).  Highlight was the Dugong (unique to Indo-west Pacific).  But the \"ride\" thru the penguins was fantastic (and unique among ALL the aquariums we have visited).\n\nLocated on Darling Harbour, it\'s a wonderful \"touristy\" area in central Sydney.  It was an easy 30 minute walk from our hotel near Hyde Park.\n\nVery friendly for wheelchairs and strollers to boot.\n\nHighly recommend!!!','2025-11-02 10:11:39','Google','2025-12-15 18:32:04'),(143,256,'Carmela Auriemma','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117460902434176667704/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIbjiHhfC6vqQIEhbn9lN1v3hairLCMRe12C4au9h8aoBz3Hg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'The aquarium is big and full of amazing marine life. It’s right next to Wild Life and Madame Tussauds, so you can easily visit all three in one morning. I recommend going early to enjoy everything without rushing. I got my tickets online with a great deal — one pass for the Aquarium, the Zoo, and the Tower Eye. Such a magical place for kids! 🐠🐧✨','2025-10-20 02:52:56','Google','2025-12-15 18:32:04'),(144,256,'A T','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116426571506828733606/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTN3E0l-rWTK_M3I8y8TMA1auYYwYav2vdrr-h4LBvZHFuJXvG=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Mesmerizing underwater world with vivid species,\ncrystal-clear tanks and immersive exhibits, well-maintained facilities and clear safety standards\nFriendly staff, informative talks, and captivating feedings\nA bit on the pricier side, but worth it for the quality experience\nPerfect for families and marine life enthusiasts,\nClose-up encounters with penguins, sharks, and rays\nConvenient location near Darling Harbour and great eateries nearby.\n\nVR experience was fantastic as well.','2025-11-30 03:16:00','Google','2025-12-15 18:32:04'),(145,256,'Lydia','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100141844679441039176/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-6n_5kUUGH6Ge6MQ-SJksgPuL6VsE64kFlNnsBZgDEZMaicRHug=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'What a fun place to play tourist in! It definately needs to be said that this aquarium beats Kelly Tarltons back in NZ... The place seemed to be well-maintained, with lots of interesting sections to see. I especially liked how each section had information about each species, as well as the addition of a touch pool. It doesn\'t take a huge amount of time to go through the entire place, however I would recommend taking your time, especially when going through the tunnel where you can see the sharms swimming above you. Overall I would say this is definately a place worth visiting on a rainy day!','2025-12-02 08:14:05','Google','2025-12-15 18:32:04'),(146,257,'Richard Shanks','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114336706671572561384/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUB7qf2qhNWA5iUWDIIyxS0H4sg-TS2L0hyGtIoi5GhDHjnO9lB=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'What an amazing journey. My Great, Great Uncle was here in the 1920s to see most of the construction of the Bridge through to its completion in 1932\n\nI brought my Uncles Great, Great, Nephew to experience the greatness of one the best bridge creations in the world.\n\nThe guide was very patient and helpful throughout the climb. The staff were courteous and mindful of the safety rules and regulations throughout the experience.\n\nDefinitely an amazing experience.\n\nThank you 🙏🏻🙂','2025-09-27 06:34:45','Google','2025-12-15 18:33:38'),(147,257,'Muhammad Sadikin','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105964083681002383094/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGdydvCBP0BeYbnIsLYUWUpG25-z9AsN3zxu0pZRinjYNj0Rfz=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Went for a Summit Climb on a weekday (Thursday, 4 Dec 2025) at the 3.45pm slot under Climb Leader Archie, which turned out to be one of the highlights of our Sydney trip. The route was straightforward with secured steps throughout, and the climb was very manageable. Although it was a hot day, the constant breeze made the experience comfortable - and we were lucky to enjoy beautifully clear weather.\n\nArchie was fantastic - warm, friendly, took great photos (do purchase the add-on as you are not allowed to bring practically anything with you on the climb) and provided meaningful insights about the Bridge and Sydney’s history. And of course, the views from the top were simply incredible.\n\nHighly recommended if you’re looking for a memorable Sydney highlight. Even if you may be afraid of heights, not to worry as the climb is gradual and you would be securely tethered - one of our party who has some fear of height was a bit apprehensive at the initial part of the climb and came out smiling at the summit.\n\nThanks again to Archie for making the climb such an enjoyable and memorable one!','2025-12-05 11:36:54','Google','2025-12-15 18:33:38'),(148,257,'Ty lee','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100277305415939644928/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURBVB5qzwVO4ldgph46f7TwaRvFXm7hugmubrJ5P9b3ijpvGIECA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'One of the memorable activities during a visit to Sydney. Very friendly and helpful staff at the customer reception. The detailed briefing and preparation for the climb was great. Awesome view of Sydney from the top of the iconic Harbour Bridge. Though the price for the guided Climb is slightly high but it\'s totally worthwhile for the amazing vibes and beautiful views from the top of the Harbour Bridge. For safety reasons cameras and handphones are not allowed to bring along for the climb. The group guide will take the photos at certain sections of the bridge climb. The photos can be purchased after the climb.','2025-09-05 04:38:00','Google','2025-12-15 18:33:38'),(149,257,'Xionghai Lee','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114921263550171709494/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK04DM0tZnXDYKLPIAfFxntV14ze6cNTS-XbnpUtI1zDigm0w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'Entire experience was nothing short of amazing. Crew briefed us well and assured us the group fully. Climb was fairly easy and pace was alright. Shy of a 5 star review as the photo package was disappointing. Photo taking skills have rooms of\nImprovement & knowing how to use the camera is important for a twilight climb.','2025-11-01 00:05:49','Google','2025-12-15 18:33:38'),(150,257,'Scott (thatdadgram)','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108496280771212535109/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_N_A0OsZ82UCkGL6eqvkbeLW_DBr6ER6YJU8s1tQbZp5gbiY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'On Thursday, the 6th of November, we embarked on a summit tour of the Sydney Harbour Bridge with Alex as our guide. Whether you’re a local, interstate visitor, or travelling from overseas, there’s no better way to see Sydney than climbing the Harbour Bridge. The tour is highly informative, interesting, and an iconic Australian experience. Alex, our guide, ensured that all her climbers were well-looked after and felt comfortable throughout the climb. The walk is accessible to people of all ages, with a small ladder climb at the beginning. I highly recommend this bucket list experience to anyone visiting Sydney! Thank you, Alex, for providing such a memorable and educational experience.','2025-11-09 09:09:52','Google','2025-12-15 18:33:38'),(151,258,'Nikita Kale','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113454491292012173329/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXu0CM3SDddASQ_A67d512FPNx8VKc_m6C1Jp97FGOThKGgNjc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'We visited the Sydney Opera House and it was an amazing experience. The architecture is stunning, with those iconic sails that look even more impressive in person. The views of Sydney Harbor and the Harbor Bridge from the steps are spectacular, especially from the ferry we took from Parramatta — such a scenic approach!\n\nOn top of that, we got to watch symphony orchestra show inside, which made the visit even more memorable. The acoustics and interior design are incredible, and the atmosphere of being in such a world-famous venue while listening to live music is something you won’t forget.\n\nOverall, it’s a must-see spot in Sydney — whether you’re there for the architecture, the harbor views, or a performance, it really delivers on all fronts.','2025-11-27 01:46:30','Google','2025-12-15 18:34:44'),(152,258,'Tim','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114769068671825584606/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3F7srHC-8EuWjAafiAJcHvSAF2670lMBwV_0wQ4NLV1PkYg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Booked the tour and dining experience for $81 weeks in advance. Tour started and ended on time with a group of around 20. Headsets were provided so that everyone can hear the live tour guide. They will ask you to check in any medium or large sizes bags or backpacks, but it\'s easy and free. Tour involved some easy, short walks and steps, but anyone can manage. Very informative and worth doing. The dining add on gives you 3 restaurant options to choose from, all very close by. There\'s a special, limited menu just for this deal. I chose Midden which had no wait for lunch time and went with the barramundi dish and pinot grigio. The fish was excellent, perfectly cooked and thoughtfully flavored. Asked for no added salt and they were able to accommodate. Wine was good as well and recommended by the server. Overall, a great tour and dining experience that\'s reasonably priced','2025-11-03 09:08:28','Google','2025-12-15 18:34:44'),(153,258,'Yolanda Gonzalez','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113056856144755362933/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdFqJaZECKC4mxI_ldDE0KBPtxGpm8WcnxKlteYu2vY37WKUDJGA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'The structure is amazing… just like the pictures you see in Internet. Easy to move around. Handicap friendly. Many spots for snacks and even for lunch or dinner. Inside is big enough to run several events at the same time. We saw The Shiralee… excellent play presentation. Buster really run the show. The terrace around the Opera offers great spots for pictures and opportunities to crash on weddings… many diverse weddings. If you have time, you can visit the Botanical Garden nearby. You can’t miss it, if you are in Sydney!','2025-11-01 10:17:25','Google','2025-12-15 18:34:44'),(154,258,'Kishan Naidu','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108106685430080484930/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLcdzwARAiS0c23PR3GmkuCj3-Bq2fHqdzONQZV31n8t2Eui5y=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Architecture that captivates your heart! I didn\'t get a chance to go inside, but honestly, the outside view is stunning enough on its own, it has its power to grab everyone\'s attention.\n\nTop Tip: If you want the best possible view, take a ferry from Circular Quay after sunset. Seeing the Opera House from the water at night is an unmissable experience.','2025-11-24 17:00:52','Google','2025-12-15 18:34:44'),(155,258,'Ira Susana','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104005932214948016572/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8zHy8X6UZ8WF1FXAgPJbMfl9BBLNW7L6d5erv92jDoFlY2JQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Of course, the iconic tourist attraction!\n\nWe usually only take pictures from the outside whenever visiting the Sydney Opera House (SOH). But Alhamdulillah this year we had the chance to watch the Australian Chamber Orchestra (ACO) performance.\n\nThe architecture is really unique. The view from inside SOP to the Harbour Bridge and the surrounding areas is breathtaking!\n\nEach performance lasted around 1.5 hours. The multimedia facility as additional modern setting adds to the amazing theatrical experience. I did not expect to watch the ACO with documentary screening as background.\n\nThere are bar and café on the main concern hall that serves drinks and light snacks.\nYou can enter from the main entrance located under the primary stairs structure, or you can enter via a door with security check-in table to right after the tourist ticketing area.\n\nThere are many concerts and arts performances for all ages, not just classical opera or orchestra as I used to think.\n\nWell, a famous landmark does not need recommendation. It speaks for itself.','2025-11-09 22:46:43','Google','2025-12-15 18:34:44'),(156,259,'Morgan Cooper','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107709178465847254965/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUP-oHHcMvaNQXTmHJji16uND0Bn-_Fcc9LRmylUB6rYt5B_1yL=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'What a beautiful view of Sydney. Highly recommend (pun intended) for anybody. Weather you are a first time visitor or life long Sydney sider to get up there at least once. This is the second time i have been up, as an ex Sydney resident i went up about 15-20 years ago, and although not much has changed in the tower itself, it has an unrivaled view of the city and surrounds, which has changed dramatically over that period. Unfortunately a bit of a smoggy day for us but still very glad we did it again.','2025-12-06 05:09:58','Google','2025-12-15 18:36:11'),(157,259,'Radovan Kramár','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115210390471042724738/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1Fi3uTuuL83XTrMT6qvCD0XbgiltqElPiI7gp5AuFhhpaTp76=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Its really nice lookout place. You can see so much from Sydney. Windows could be cleaned up better but I believe that its quite hard to maintain place with so many visitors. But there is still space to improve :) We bought tickets on arrival and they let us in a moment.','2025-11-24 08:40:28','Google','2025-12-15 18:36:11'),(158,259,'Pillappan K','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107907990488854972165/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWy2Q5Qp4bC0-sMwlQ9_YeRhzAdrPQEc1JCoAoo7N2WWcwPaQoBOQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',5,'80 storeyed tower with an o servation deck on the top giving a 360 degree view fo Sydney tower including the harbor.  Popular with tourists for watching the sun set on Sydney. Otherwise too it is popular. The observation deck is closed with glass.. there is skywalking facility too for additional cost. A coffee shop is also available at top.','2025-12-06 19:41:45','Google','2025-12-15 18:36:11'),(159,259,'Moniqua','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114619384527784280763/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1kxf1TfoxSX2mpBrCLYwR68xzRsgjZaJQFXI9tYpllq9aEgg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Breathtaking! I could have circled around several more times not taking pictures just admiring the beauty God created in the sky. Very grateful I could catch the sunset. Great value with the three attraction pass, but would have been a great value alone as well.','2025-11-26 10:56:19','Google','2025-12-15 18:36:11'),(160,259,'Morgana “MoNa” Q','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105049192312177802990/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDQLqsHbC9NJvFmesTM0XChjPb4AmVyM9U7p7yJgkxC2A20ih0Zw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Sydney Tower Eye is a must-see!\n\nThe views from the top are absolutely breathtaking, and you can see the entire city, the harbour, and even the coastline. We did the sunset visit, and it was incredible — less crowded, peaceful, and the colors over Sydney were just beautiful.\n\nThe whole experience was smooth and family-friendly. A perfect way to take in the beauty of Sydney!','2025-11-26 06:49:27','Google','2025-12-15 18:36:11'),(161,260,'Saurav PRASAIN','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114555791206165352515/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINZElH4kA2QwZoy3wyqvln73m2RjaeOCszkv7rDxObGEEsYg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'I visited Taronga Zoo today with my big family, and it was my second time there. This is definitely one of the must-do experiences in Sydney. The vibes were amazing!\n\nWe went around midday, which isn’t really the ideal time to visit. If you want to see the animals more active and relaxed, it’s better to go either in the morning or later in the afternoon. That way, you’ll have a better chance of spotting most of them — including the lions. We did manage to see the lion, but only for a short while.\n\nThe seal show was absolutely amazing — you can’t afford to miss it! The energy, tricks, and connection between the trainers and seals were so fun to watch.\n\nMy kids absolutely loved it — from the animals to the shows, they were excited the whole time. It’s such a great place for families to spend the day together.\n\nIt was so much fun overall — from boarding the ferry to the very last moment. I missed taking the cable car on the way back, which I really recommend because it offers stunning views of Sydney Harbour and the Opera House.\n\nSuch a great experience — can’t wait to go again!','2025-11-11 12:00:15','Google','2025-12-15 18:37:06'),(162,260,'Annie Chen','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114609303171358578586/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcCA1QhlnCyO3iBQe9CwWeHrjJGmhBU4JlwHrbMuYBh9P8l9w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'It was great seeing all the animals. The views to Sydney harbour is an added bonus! Been here a few times already with friends and family and it’s a great activity. Highly recommend if you want to see a variety of zoo animals. The Gorilla was the highlight for me, just sitting there and eating calmly.','2025-11-25 03:52:12','Google','2025-12-15 18:37:06'),(163,260,'Ann Christopherson','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115082320030346521447/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvd0eYFCV7UJcr5RVkG8H13EechDflKsCyf7Hx7mWFnVQJungo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Beautiful Zoo. The glass front enclosures gave a better look at the animals. In some areas, animals could walk right up to you on a walkway. Clean beautiful zoo! Get tickets in advance for a better rate. The ferry ride over added to the fun!','2025-12-02 20:53:58','Google','2025-12-15 18:37:06'),(164,260,'Perry Campbell','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107269972243173236918/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXj8DhfHOG3EFUcKN8tpKrdSI4ZggX7smfnpf7fLJrcrjoVMN7-=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'What a great day out. A 10am talk about the Lions, a seal show at 11am, then a birds of flight show at 12noon. Sit at the top end of either corner if you want to be a volunteer and gold some birds. Amazing show definately great experience. If u have zoo membership its affordable. Food prices are crazy so byo if you can. Enter from the top entrance. Ferry and bus easy to get there. Best to be early opens at 9.30am to beat the crowds and do the firat shows of the day.','2025-12-04 12:43:59','Google','2025-12-15 18:37:06'),(165,260,'Chris Brownlee','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113634260066587712294/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVal0QnJGD5dro0NY7m8Hj_qdy3SaK_Ii50etMu_jsdc8qb-pGa=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Roar and Snore might be on the higher price end for some but it is totally worth it!! You get so much, private tours, beautiful food, plenty of drinks, more tours on the night walk, an amazing glamping experience, with air con! Breakfast, more tours and walks, even feeding the giraffes !! I loved hearing the lions roar while I was waking up, such a surreal experience. Can’t wait to do it again!','2025-11-28 18:54:16','Google','2025-12-15 18:37:06'),(166,261,'Annie Rodriguez','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102379628286431750221/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWi_AXf4bKasH_d_qzKdDHZEs-pSo2Wc5sWQ9krFYJROvqh3_EFUQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Great place to spend the day with the family even on a budget you can take your own snacks and spend the days with the kiddos. There’s fun activities for everybody in the family. There’s lockers to put away your belongings and if you forget any of the essentials, they have a store with everything you may need . There’s plenty of spaces just for the little ones . There is alcohol and delicious treats.\n. Plenty of free setting areas and Reserved spaces for purchase. Clean friendly, please to have a fun day and go home to plan the next trip back to adventure island.','2025-09-27 04:23:18','Google','2025-12-15 18:38:33'),(167,261,'bonniegotyou','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107247421157850246902/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIskUHD8DkLd6ywzu04GdMfirSYTuiUgYG2DcyyUFamSkr4aQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'I took my youngest son here for his 13th birthday. We had a BLAST! The staff was excellent, which has been my experience at all parks owned and operated by Busch Gardens/SeaWorld. The dining pass was easy to use. Our cabana had a fridge and water in it, as well as a ceiling fan. At one slide, I was struggling to get the heavy raft up the stairs. Due to it being slow at the time, the lifeguard at the top, came down and carried the raft the rest of the way for me. Sebastian was our favorite. The lifeguards rotate ever 30ish minutes or so, so you get to see them at different attractions throughout the day. Sebastian was so pleasant and seemed like he enjoyed being there. He took the time to introduce himself and interact with us wherever we saw him. What a gem!','2025-09-28 13:06:31','Google','2025-12-15 18:38:33'),(168,261,'Franny Bae','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107229989816014635692/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDrBKw8cVnEuKMjaGzGTHcx5TePmDPt21j2ylwMdJhkkiE5AZHvg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'This park was so nice. I love that they had different play areas for the kids. One of them adults can enjoy just as much. They have slides and so many water works. There was a huge bucket that would fill up and an alarm would sound and it would tip over. My son didn’t like this area too much because all the water spewing everywhere. The wave pool was his favorite play areas. We were there 90% of our day. There were so many things to do your child will not be bored. I recommend the dining pass because it saves much money if you are there for long and want to eat. They have water fountains available. They just did not have any funnel cake. They have plenty of sitting areas and shade so no problem with finding an area to relax in.','2025-07-02 19:56:36','Google','2025-12-15 18:38:33'),(169,261,'Kaylie Craig','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103517376324754229762/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIT_Row1rzzNWZtJmBG-ExgSW2_mLofHeDocc--YGoUqg3CYw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'We had a blast at Adventure Island Water Park! The thrill rides and attractions were a hit with our family. However, our experience was slightly marred by the All-Day Dining option. Only three restaurants participated, and the food quality was subpar, especially at Surfside Cafe. We ordered four meals, but one was missing, and we had to wait over 20 minutes for it to arrive. To make matters worse, the burger patty was frozen solid. Despite this, we still had a great time and would recommend the park to others. Hopefully, they\'ll work on improving their dining options.','2025-10-25 00:49:27','Google','2025-12-15 18:38:33'),(170,261,'eli Flores','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104095368161714930868/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLfjYIVY2DIlxCK4h3KJYLWumS7Ihka1RqSH2d05Zoru4TT8w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'We love this place so much that came back the same week! We rent a cabana both time and was peaceful y convenient for the kids to relax and eat after attractions. Mango Joe\'s food was great 20/20 the personal beautiful from the chef to the cashier. Great customer service and the bar drink was a plus! The kids had a blast and we enjoyed every part of it. Definitely coming back!','2025-08-24 03:13:17','Google','2025-12-15 18:38:33'),(171,262,'Elietty Devesa','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112290129662661242806/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEUDhGQsjc56DrwUygTyjwfe42oRhh7hSLpqUmlyU-rBlmjKk1yQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'I have a lot to say as I want this to be a honest review.\nFirst off I feel this park is mostly for adults. 70% of the rides are roller coasters, and most are pretty fast with crazy loops. If you do not like roller coasters I feel it might not be worth it. I went on 4 roller coasters in total and by the end I could not handle another one as much as I wanted to experience everything its just a lot of intense rides and if you are not used it or are a big fan this might not be the best park in my personal opinion.\nHowever, the park itself is like a little world you get to explore. There are animals and beautiful plants. Also different areas with different themes and decorations. I did feel walking around was also enjoyable.\nThe food was so overpriced my jaw dropped. $52 for two orders of chicken wings with fries and two cokes. If you can get the deal of all day dinning it might be worth it. Food was okay none the less but for the price not worth it.\nParking is $40 and you get to take a tram free of charge to the park entrance.\nIf you bought your ticket online entering is quick and easy, just scan the code with an employee.\nOverall, I enjoyed my time with my husband and I had a great time.','2025-11-28 02:00:43','Google','2025-12-15 18:39:53'),(172,262,'Shaili Singh','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109265841489314613538/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVc-aCOCEhLpqcaxi-d_tuPKHvx0NiOKT-NxGmLPWxRlabD86g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Such a great theme park and very underrated. Beautiful themeing throughout the park with really fun & thrilling coasters. Plus really cool animal interactions. The safari is about $40 and includes a chance to feed lettuce to a giraffe... really fun and unique experience. The food is ok - better than Sea World (even though they are in the same family) - more choices, especially for vegetarians, and the layout of places to eat was much better too!','2025-11-28 19:56:54','Google','2025-12-15 18:39:53'),(173,262,'Alex Koller','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115358538203282774467/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmNPU227C7T44Z2TRgOPXob1yiJyXTDeGJIhvDfHMUqL8Gu7QsCA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Busch Gardens blew me away on my recent visit! The holiday décor was stunning—festive, detailed, and honestly more impressive than what I’ve seen at Disney lately. The food and beverage selection was excellent too, with tons of flavorful options and great seasonal drinks that made the experience feel extra special.\n\nThe park has clearly invested in major upgrades. Everything felt cleaner, more modern, and much more thoughtfully designed. Plus, there are a ton of awesome rides for both thrill-seekers and young kids, along with multiple playgrounds for all ages—perfect for families who need a breather between attractions.\n\nOverall, Busch Gardens has really stepped up its game. The improvements, atmosphere, and value easily put it on a level that rivals—and in many ways surpasses—Disney. Highly recommend!','2025-11-25 16:55:59','Google','2025-12-15 18:39:53'),(174,262,'Lanique Nel','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114859435282234122117/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQiLg6_r275_CtbOFOC4llrQLCFk0E94J4EP5IHrjv1a0ztUuw7Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'We had such a great time at Busch Gardens Tampa! The park was super quiet when we visited, which made the experience even better - we were able to go on all the rides multiple times without waiting in long lines. It felt like we had the park almost to ourselves.\n\nThe highlight of the day was definitely the newest coaster, Iron Gwazi. It’s an absolute must-ride - fast, smooth, and full of thrills from start to finish. We couldn’t get enough of it and rode it several times!\n\nOverall, the park was clean, well-run, and offered a perfect mix of excitement and relaxation. If you get the chance to visit on a quieter day, you’re in for an unforgettable experience.','2025-10-14 18:46:34','Google','2025-12-15 18:39:53'),(175,262,'William Price','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110809969481387867850/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUyib5zPmJx5VgXBq-bLXwFe-RtzG6HdSV03NO6YFohu58KKjuSXw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Busch Gardens Tampa Bay\n\nI brought my family—old and young—from out of town, and this was my first time visiting during the holiday season. Busch Gardens really surprised me. They have so many festive setups and picture spots all throughout the park, it honestly feels like a holiday photoshoot destination and amusement park in one.\n\nWhat makes Busch Gardens unique is how it blends a full amusement park with a zoo experience. One minute you’re riding roller coasters, the next you’re up close with animals—it’s something you don’t get at most parks.\n\nMy whole family had a great time, and the holiday atmosphere made it even better. Definitely worth the trip during the festive season. 🎄🌟','2025-11-25 09:01:44','Google','2025-12-15 18:39:53'),(176,263,'Danielle Morrison - Tampa FL','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101369552551807298271/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXkP6TzZOJ5VFhTOraat_EuWu51Wf5Zo3fn5GXAnirwK1GetYg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'We had such a fantastic evening with Tampa Bay Fun Boat for our recent realtor networking event! The crew was absolutely wonderful — especially Captain Darrell. They had coolers, ice, and water ready for us, played excellent music, and set off right on time. We cruised into the sunset with a perfect breeze and then toured downtown to admire the beautiful Tampa skyline.\n\nOur group of 30 had plenty of space to walk around, mingle, and enjoy the evening, and the bimini top provided welcome shade while the sun was still out. It was the perfect setup for our out-of-town guests to experience Tampa from the water.\n\nThank you so much to the Tampa Bay Fun Boat team for helping us create such a successful and memorable event. We’ll definitely be booking with you again for future outings!','2025-09-26 15:43:46','Google','2025-12-15 18:41:20'),(177,263,'C R','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106914173617258896033/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaPQNULyJKeXJJ2Xki6_E1yevwwpLBcHLIYKY6UPuCMNmCb2Vs=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'I had a wonderful experience with Tampa Bay Fun Boat! 🛥️The captain was incredibly knowledgeable about the history of Tampa Bay and shared so many interesting facts along the way. 💙He was also very friendly, which made the tour even more enjoyable.\nThe views of the bay were absolutely beautiful🏙️ such a relaxing and fun way to explore the area. Highly recommend this company if you\'re visiting Tampa! 🌟🌟🌟','2025-08-18 18:27:00','Google','2025-12-15 18:41:20'),(178,263,'Romit Sen','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100051798409850358105/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4FksW3UCYVCnT5yuXOs3qUMrOWhvkt6rxNDrwjt4JS9RybRb3_A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Had a really great time!! A very beautiful experience - Captain Darryl was a really great host, and he’s an amazing photographer!! The shared pictures are what you get to see on the boat ride!','2025-11-25 15:04:38','Google','2025-12-15 18:41:20'),(179,263,'Halea Secor','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105467369107767946037/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLQIn1fvJWrjBvRqDG0eBQkd7cOYeRJAGIopJDqXlmxUbDsOUE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'This was a great boat tour for a great price. The boat was smaller so there was a more intimate feel. We saw dolphins and a beautiful sunset. Captain Lee and Captain Darrel were funny, knowledgeable, and gave an insider view of the Tampa area. We would 100% come back and do this tour again.','2025-09-29 13:20:22','Google','2025-12-15 18:41:20'),(180,263,'Andrew Stastny','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109416816427296943659/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-IOspmlNN0eC5AwhEzK7SvVUqXp7Nc4Vcz2F5-l7Fsh9EhRKAkg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Sooo much fun! Low-key and chill ‘tour’ of Tampa Bay around Davis Islands. Captain Lee & Mate JT did an excellent job providing narration of the important sites and music along the way! BYOB gave it a casual feel! As long-time residents in Tampa my family highly recommends the Tampa Bay Fun Boat for a sunset or anytime boat ride tour of Tampa Bay!','2025-08-10 02:28:54','Google','2025-12-15 18:41:20'),(181,264,'Kennedy','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112348190832031212598/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVE9zG9ZGyAAGlUyQOh7NKzfVMyDEMhJUOnw-lUoiZQIetZ4Zit=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'I would consider this the ultimate kid getaway. There’s so many areas for imaginary play and enough to do for kids to get the wiggles out. You can easily spend the entire day here. I think this museum is more appropriate for children younger than 8-10 years. Older kids may be disinterested because the activities are more for toddlers & little kids. We enjoyed story time and building a gingerbread house while we were there, and food items were pretty inexpensive. The museum was very clean and has sanitizer stations all over. Finally, the staff was very helpful, friendly and engaging with the kids. I would definitely return again.','2025-11-26 12:32:45','Google','2025-12-15 18:42:35'),(182,264,'Dennis C','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108917699804650261462/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWQlmt2sPIFQENwTQvYea3HAaKYWm4HiSZa9gYdyrQ6J0fY7uU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Glazer\'s Children Museum is a great venue to take your children to if you\'re ever in the heart of downtown Tampa, Florida. It\'s in a great location, sitting between the Tampa-Hillsborough Public Library, Tampa Museum of Art, and the Curtis Hixon Waterfront Park. So while making the Glazer\'s Museum the main event, you can take your children to the park or along the Tampa Riverwalk afterwards.\n\nWith the William F Poe (Poe) Parking Garage conveniently located next to it, you can enjoy a relatively hassle-free drive to the venue. You pay for the parking up front. While there is no parking fee waive with the museum, you\'re spending approximately $3 an hour for parking that has overhead protection and is fairly secured.\n\nLike most other children\'s museums around the nation, Glazer\'s is suited for toddlers to children approximately 5 years of age. The themes and areas may not necessarily be appealing to anyone older than that.\n\nAnd like most other children\'s museums, the areas and \"exhibits\" are centered around the aspects of daily life (such as supermarkets, doctors, veterinarians, farms, etc.) With that being said, the Glazer\'s Children Museum is a spacious three-stories in size. I came here with my youngest on a Saturday, and while there was a steady stream of families through the venue, I never felt too cramped or crowded.\n\nOn the first floor, you\'ll find a small store along with a food court area. There is also a rather large elevator to accommodate multiple families with strollers which is quite nice. It is also where you will find the first museum area/exhibit. It is a sizeable water exhibit so the kids naturally gravitate toward it. Prepare to get wet, but have no fear they do provide a limited number of splash bibs!\n\nThere is also a set of stairs that ranges all the levels of the museum, if you don\'t want to use the elevator. What immediately stands out with the Glazer\'s Children Museum over most other children\'s museums is the hanging \"climber\" (essentially a transparent maze of various level platforms that your child can safely navigate through) and a section on the second floor, aptly named \"Forts\" (this is where your kids can essentially play and build forts from the usual household furniture and furnishings.\n\nThe third floor is dedicated to their dinosaur/Triceratops exhibits. It\'s actually pretty cool if you find yourself geeking out over dinos.\n\nAlso with the reciprocal membership from another venue, admission to Glazer\'s in the month of October was entirely free. Overall, a great place to visit at least once with your young children!','2025-10-06 10:05:37','Google','2025-12-15 18:42:35'),(183,264,'Serge El-Khazen','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102619922920458240186/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBMB7XzIvjmZwW_yTHs3kuj-E9CccL1er9JuStjEwg7LwyHwk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'The Glazer Children’s Museum in Tampa is a fantastic spot for younger kids to play, explore, and learn. The exhibits are super interactive, our favorite was the water play area and the pretend grocery store. Everything is hands-on and designed to spark creativity and imagination. The museum is clean, well-organized, and the staff is very friendly and helpful. It’s best suited for kids under 9, and there’s plenty to keep them busy for hours. The location is great too, right by the Riverwalk and a park where you can continue the fun outside. It’s definitely worth a visit if you’re in Tampa with little ones. Admission fees are a bit pricey for what they offer but we had a great time and will absolutely be coming back!','2025-08-06 20:39:52','Google','2025-12-15 18:42:35'),(184,264,'Fairy tale author Edda','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116316065256625408448/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXPphyetwIUJfyz-pG57iCXaux_OMp8IJ0qu1okhtqm0SzdC72=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Wonderful museum. Big John has captivated my son who loves dinosaurs. The first floor has a water ride and the second floor has many different \"rooms\" from a farm to an old house. It was fun. paid parking $20 per day','2025-06-26 15:11:29','Google','2025-12-15 18:42:35'),(185,264,'Kristopher Farmer','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116805108009185755221/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAcj20dNEAhuY30i-rC8bUbgOftkhGJF_V8bK96tNfpNr3Gg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'My daughter is 14 months & she absolutely loved it! Parking was $30.00 downtown but other then that yhe musuem was amazing! We will be back!','2025-10-06 11:09:06','Google','2025-12-15 18:42:35'),(186,265,'Sergio Murgas','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111314163774132550537/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSMMG-qUHRny65vtjPLVae76p2IRi2mg_lRpsW6OjDaKYMTmb5=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'Visiting the Henry B. Plant Museum feels like stepping into another century. Located inside the historic Plant Hall at the University of Tampa, this place beautifully preserves the legacy of the Gilded Age and the vision of Henry B. Plant — the man who brought luxury and innovation to Tampa.\n\nThe architecture is stunning — from the silver minarets and grand arches to the elegant interiors filled with original furniture and art. Every room tells a story, and the attention to detail is simply breathtaking. You can almost imagine the glamorous guests who once stayed here when it was the Tampa Bay Hotel.\n\nThe museum is small but incredibly well curated. The staff is friendly and passionate about history, and the exhibits provide a clear picture of how Tampa evolved thanks to the railroad and tourism. It’s not just a museum — it’s a window into Florida’s past.\n\nPerfect for history lovers, architecture enthusiasts, or anyone looking for a quiet cultural experience in the heart of Tampa. Don’t miss the chance to walk through this iconic landmark — it’s timeless.','2025-10-16 13:35:54','Google','2025-12-15 18:43:58'),(187,265,'Hannah Huguenin','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114827478034683237424/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSNYJuxkI2OaAq1kj1kcT_z2guo2L3JVZ061CEG2YwL5mQYXSWKQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc