 also got licked on the back of neck by a giraffe 🦒 named Patty.','2025-09-29 03:11:01','Google','2025-12-15 18:48:07'),(204,268,'Kelly Black','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117261731648144894115/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW72u4bFf9k2QxmmVLwAC_hJHFlK5BtPXzsdhuMsKRivM8fnAEfWw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'What a delight! A little pricey if you are not a pass holder. But it\'s a fun experience. You go through the park and see all of the animals. The tour guides are knowledgeable and fun! I have done this multiple times and the giraffes never disappoint! Good for most ages. You stand up on the back of a moving truck and hold in. Some bumps along the way. It\'s also handicapable friendly.','2025-03-12 22:04:25','Google','2025-12-15 18:48:07'),(205,268,'Bonnie Palmitesto','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117114951644020455612/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBy0x0Lx7rFEjmlo1XQpT2kTqpVY34Iv0M7TxrulBY-ayAICtN=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'My daughter and I enjoyed ourselves. Great if you are interested in getting more informed about the animals and their care.','2025-11-04 14:36:14','Google','2025-12-15 18:48:07'),(206,269,'Andrea Kletschka','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104526478056593849600/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKA8GjcnwEzmsM-dDDMt8X8Pk-ZphF6Oj0DLBwPtz-8D0wWoA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'DO IT!!! This was an Amazing experience! Captain Scott is a blast and makes the whole trip memorable! We had zero boating experience and had no problem from start to finish. Captain Scott made it so much more than a speed boat drive! He’s a hoot and you can tell he loves what he does. We can’t wait to do this tour again!','2024-01-31 18:05:32','Google','2025-12-15 18:49:28'),(207,269,'Daniel Adams','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113801941094710206069/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW8tUFYKsjNaiCrsWqccMmwPPkC0fzMxuQJH7hdOIsOc1WKetVMpw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Do you think you have done everything well? How about adding the ability to drive a speed boat to your list? Well, that\'s exactly what I did. This was just flipping amazing. The location is a little off the beaten path. However, it has a beautiful beach right next to it, so if you show up early enough or stay after, there is basically a \"local\" beach, and it\'s beautiful. You want to show up a little early for the safety briefing and to take some great pics. You can bring whatever except alcohol or weapons so if you want to bring some water you can. I had no idea, so I didn\'t. Also, I would recommend great pockets or a fanny pack because you can\'t set your phone on the seat as it will slide into the back of the boat and be gone.  I put mine in my shorts pocket between pics and videos. This is so cool. You are taught by a wonderful captain who has 30+ years of experience in the industry. \"Bring some cash to tip him\" He will lead you on a jet ski into the open water waters of Tampa Bay. You will get almost 45 minutes of high-speed boating excitement. Make sure to watch for any waves and follow all the tips and rules you learn in the beginning, and you will have a time of your life. You will go past places you can\'t see on land and experience going under bridges while being able to say, \"I know how to drive a boat now.\" That\'s a bucket list if you ask me. I would highly recommend this thrilling adventure next time you are in Tampa. It really is like a Segway tour with speedboats!!! I went when it was like 65 degrees out, and with the sun, it was perfect. I recommend sunscreen and maybe a secure hot in the summertime. You must try this, though!! If this review helped you at all, please mark as helpful and follow me for more reviews around the world.','2024-03-24 03:00:42','Google','2025-12-15 18:49:28'),(208,269,'Faith Ebersole','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117375346919344460629/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWF0GELvAfx2-6AGgrKuMYNA7kv83YZ6mZQrExWBpfozVUgDzQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'We had a great time! The water and weather was perfect, and they are right, you don\'t really get wet on this. My only suggestion would be that it would be nice if the guide talked a bit more on the speaker on when we should be speeding up or slowing down, we were in idle speed for awhile where no one seemed to know if we should/allowed to start going faster and can\'t really see the instructors hand signals from so far away. Also wasn\'t super sure if I was harming the boats in anyway from switching from speeding up/slowing down/idle too much or too quickly. The parts where we were in open water and could go fast were the best! We will be doing more activities like this in the future for sure 💖','2021-08-23 04:19:12','Google','2025-12-15 18:49:28'),(209,269,'Stephanie Sarkissian','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107323687166437406797/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTOYrBTRXGYfbBPNaOWxtXzGYA6R0hiUQaullnOTAAft8d_UGjsg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Took my wife for her birthday and we had so much fun! Captain Scott is so fun and very knowledgeable. The boats pick up some speed and are fun to drive! We also saw lots of dolphins! 🐬 Great day out on the water. Make sure you hydrate and wear sunscreen!','2024-06-22 19:58:12','Google','2025-12-15 18:49:28'),(210,269,'Robin Dukes','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118412086717714699610/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPXc1-muQUpQaTxdhfsgVQxVG4Pv0RkCgGRy7ofW5I76NW4osQow=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'What an amazing experience!!\nScott was a phenomenal tour guide, he was funny, knowledgeable and patient. I now have a greater love for speed boats and will be back with the family.','2023-12-27 18:32:57','Google','2025-12-15 18:49:28'),(211,270,'Toni Thompson','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103044716430169564503/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsC5sb8GxnutzgVVz2ZAFhF6rcmkqAp3-axRmoxb59AvkODsvwpA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8',5,'Today my grandson and I enjoyed a full day and did not see everything.  We purchased the one day with all 2026 admission included.  The Christmas holiday permeates the zoo that is usually open til\n5pm with special evening holiday event by separate  admission or members free\nWe loved the Aftica section with elephants, white rhinos, hippos, giraffes, and less usual a smiles like Okapi and Tapir.\nWe were sad that the train was not working today but my grandson loved the children’s ride with Outback cars and banana airplane ride. The carousel with a dragon and elephant were a hit. Over and over\nThe areas for animals were divided by continent and with a Florida section.\nSeveral food selections offered pizzas, popcorn, canned alcohol, bottle beverages often in 100% recycled containers.\nI found a hot dog eatery with hot dogs and sausage under $11.  Delicious\nMen’s women’s and family Restrooms were located throughout the park, with a dedicated wheel chair accessible stall with grab bars and 4ftx6 ft space. Restroom doors were push and heavy to open.  A touch pad opening would be helpful for some visitors inc the woman  in a wheelchair that I held the door for— and she agreed about the touch pad.\nThe zoo is mostly accessible except at some rides and kids playground.\nToday 3 employees went above and beyond.  LAURA at customer service understood my mistake in not bringing my phone charger and charged my phone so I could drive my electric vehicle.\nJACOB at Kona Ice answered my question about their service project.  he talked so proudly about Kona Ice that I thought he was the owner, but he is a proud employee.\nCARLO was the most awesome docent at the giraffes.\nMy grandson got a blister and crying hysterically near one of the shops. DESTINEY offered bandaids and ointment.  She maintained complete calm while he screamed, with no judgement. She asked if he wanted some ice cream and gave him a small amount. That gesture really comforted him.\nGreat experience today.  Just be aware, the exit is through the gift shop','2025-11-26 01:49:47','Google','2025-12-15 18:50:43'),(212,270,'Brooke “siayla” Foster','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106001031614843761294/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYporT2ccGOREhsxI0XzjjgWXi1FWH0f5vO0dDgoSn9D-I-LyG3Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Our favourite zoo in North America. It is laid out very nicely so you can get up close to almost every animal enclosure. The staff are very knowledgeable and helpful and caring about the animals. Love the zoo also love the playgrounds and splash pads for the younger kids. Fun for the whole family.','2025-12-02 15:43:00','Google','2025-12-15 18:50:43'),(213,270,'Priscilla Dark','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106946400930803263655/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIer-KU5LoJBn67sdQK0HaWgLn-nEDBksRUmIUaZUxyXC46XQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'What a fantastic zoo!! My family is in town visiting from out of state. We used our reciprocal zoo membership to visit. I told my husband about halfway thru the day that if we didn’t have our membership and had paid full price it would’ve still been worth visiting. The kids and us had a blast! The zoo was very clean, the exhibits seemed spacious and the animals seemed happy and well cared for. The rides throughout the park, water play area and playground were an unexpected added bonus! We will definitely be back the next time we’re in town.','2025-11-18 04:57:57','Google','2025-12-15 18:50:43'),(214,270,'Gavin Hamill','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112796573612652145782/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYlpuNBWBkWU664l7xNuHMXJSGfVwJB_xznkqNdnGQfVsuxISccg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'LOVE LOVE LOVE LOVE THIS ZOO!!!!We came here during the week on a Wednesday in October during the day time and it was not crowded at all we had the time of our lives, i went up on to 6 or 7 different zoo keepers and asked tons of questions about the animals we were near and every single one of them answered my questions with ease and were super friendly. There was one zookeeper named Joe who was near the Orangutans and he was so knowledgeable and kind talked to for almost 15 minutes and knew every single question i had to ask. Plenty of water fountains and shady areas to cool off in. Safari Ride was a must! Devin was our guide on the ride .He was awesome very informative and super personable.There wasn’t a single question i asked that he could not answer with additional information on top of it. Every animal was active and visible but with the exception of one or two and if you go to lots of zoos you know that’s just apart of it but it was nice to see how the zoo made sure the animals could be comfortable and visible at the same time. Loved the Free Encounters they do with the Manatees and the Other Animals.We watched the one with the Orangutan and you HAVE to do this when you come!!You get to see them up close and have a great view and it’s a surreal experience being so close to them and we didn’t have to pay anything extra to do so.You also HAVE TO FEED THE LORIKEETS!!!! Since it was slow that day the Kind Lady who worked the Enclosure gave us a bit extra food when feeding since there was no one waiting behind us. It’s little things like that make It feel so personable and enjoyable. We also went thru the Dinosaur area And OH MY GOSH WAS IT SO COOL. They have life size dinosaurs you can get right up next too that are animatronic and so life like.Im an adult and felt like i was 10 years old again it was amazing! 10/10 Would recommend visiting here. I didn’t meet a single staff member who wasn’t friendly as can be and Also SUPER KNOWLEDGEABLE.Food and drinks are widely avaible everywhere. We had A Pizzafor lunch in the africa area that tasted great! Overall 10/10 i got my moneys worth and can’t wait to come back!!!','2025-10-08 19:01:32','Google','2025-12-15 18:50:43'),(215,270,'Charles Drake','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114615709643670677271/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRwWRtXY_UdzxV3CUgLy2-jbKdbm4gQjpsO5Rtzl4km3sl8KA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'I have been to a few different cities Zoos but this is one of the better ones for sure. They got a great selection of animals and activities for all ages. They got a show on Disney + called Secrets of the Zoo: Tampa, if you want to check it out before going to ZooTampa. There are a ton of food options and different animal experiences as well. I would recommend signing up for the experiences in advance to make sure there is availability the day you want to go. They have added a dinosaur exhibit and they also do theme events during the holidays. If you live in the Tampa Bay Area, I would recommend buying the pay for the day pass because you can come back as much as you want for a year.','2025-10-21 21:57:21','Google','2025-12-15 18:50:43'),(216,271,'Traveling Triceratop','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117476989676556242208/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFQH586XVUNjFwHhryashHdWoDm6jg11s4jNI00IoxK_L1Awk7=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Such a beautiful aquarium! I loved all of the exhibits. They have cool enclosures for all of the birds and where the lemurs are at. The big tank had lots of cool fish and sharks! They also have an octopus which I thought was pretty cool. It was a fun experience and was not too crazy busy for a Saturday. Definitely glad they had the trolley that brought us right to it too, very convenient!','2025-10-19 22:50:35','Google','2025-12-15 18:51:55'),(217,271,'Yvette Bronner','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103168247677556405636/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLSwBwz2cPXOQcOy04YDa3TQSkkOF_ogwiCCY-G3zTUFMub2g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'Lovely experience visiting the aquarium. Fun thing to do if your visiting. It took us alittle less than 2hrs to get through  it all. My 