s a really nice experience. The acoustic is good for music.','2025-11-01 13:27:54','Google','2025-12-15 19:00:24'),(247,277,'CityScrolls','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111519204745516453895/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4OIabw5P96_uY9IICqaQjfXNYRMo7YqyopN2Hr3CeKz4SObk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Here\'s a common misconception: while many associate the Vivaldi Church with the composer\'s work, the current building was actually constructed after his death. It stands adjacent to the Ospedale della Pietà, the very institution where Vivaldi mentored and dedicated most of his life to music.\n\nThe interior of the church is best experienced by attending an evening concert, when you can admire Tiepolo\'s ceiling fresco while the uplifting rendition of \'The Four Seasons\' fills the church space.','2025-06-12 14:46:56','Google','2025-12-15 19:00:24'),(248,277,'Kate','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116446472636027576078/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJfY3UW9ockmvK7bKK2wbYOp8GDXYCSD0jYRJLRtx9np0suzA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'A fantastic classical music experience in a beautiful church setting. The concert was well organized overall, though there was a bit of confusion during the intermission. The pew seating wasn’t the most comfortable, but the quality of the performance more than made up for it. The musicians played with such passion and precision that the music gave me goosebumps. A truly memorable evening for any classical music lover. Highly recommend!!','2025-11-08 14:04:25','Google','2025-12-15 19:00:24'),(249,277,'Juan Rios','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110494649879665058507/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbc7AxSwaEFJwWczMEUNq7BmJyRfJhccJ8SoDW4FOejvOZ0RkZAg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Came here for a concert, very nice place. Sitting is limited so come early so you can sit in the front. A different experience out of the ordinary.','2025-11-22 18:52:56','Google','2025-1