es here as well, in case you want to learn more in detail.\nGive yourself about 2 hours here.','2025-11-01 05:57:10','Google','2025-12-15 19:01:33'),(253,278,'Genevieve Johnson','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103299452021231504639/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvhqOltzw-DjdiBGZ0O8iNRQbaIOy22JFCPueGjpzhCkgU3JHhDg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'A must-see in Venice!\nThe Doge’s Palace is absolutely breathtaking — filled with history, incredible art, and ornate architecture that captures the essence of Venice’s power and beauty. We visited around 5 PM, and it wasn’t busy at all, which made it even more enjoyable to explore at our own pace.\n\nHighly recommend booking tickets in advance to skip any lines and ensure your preferred time. Walking across the Bridge of Sighs and seeing the view from both sides was unforgettable. Truly one of the highlights of our trip!','2025-10-16 11:03:36','Google','2025-12-15 19:01:33'),(254,278,'Tania Hamayun','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115035024424571163514/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnza_g0Jz5GZEt5oTdapV0bPlJX0AsGzJB2PriUeObxgABbxdu=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'This place was extremely extraordinary and was a pleasure exploring the palace. I would really recommend that you buy tickets beforehand and the earlier the better. You will definitely need 2+ hours to explore this palace especially if your into art and history. I loved every bit of it. The cafe was also nice and the prices were reasonable. It’s definitely a must go if you’re in Venice!','2025-10-02 06:44:48','Google','2025-12-15 19:01:33'),(255,278,'Vince.K','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104054822339124739920/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJOm9IJ0oamoostMfLBR-crkw_DDO8MXng6sFKBcTr60DFJpY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'This palace is beautiful and full of history and artwork. I recommend buying tickets ahead of time and giving yourself at least two hours to explore. I recommend getting a tour guide to learn more about the history of the palace. The café was also nice and not too expensive. It’s a must see when in Venice.','2025-10-27 19:13:45','Google','2025-12-15 19:01:33'),(256,279,'Marlo Pelysz','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115836567621922284390/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW00XJhndXv-1yVsrZd-yu2c3lkIH84HGVYOtfxwoP0HNicdYkjdg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Absolutely one of the best tours I’ve ever taken — it was everything the tour description said it would be, and more. Francesco was the perfect guide: He got the small group acquainted quickly, so by lunch we were all looking out for each other. He made extra stops along the way so we’d all be able to capture the perfect memory shot of the Dolomites and even did an unscheduled stop for the most amazing gelato.\nI cannot recommend him, the Dolomites tour or Avventure Bellissime enough!','2025-10-14 15:37:03','Google','2025-12-15 19:03:20'),(257,279,'John DelSignore','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100678206324486518834/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWr-kyLt1ZEBfwcGM7sAxa7aZfYWHflHJm9JjlTxTPQIV__BeeZ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'**Unforgettable Italian Adventure Thanks to Avventure Bellissime**\n\nOur family of five just returned from an absolutely incredible two-week journey through Italy, all perfectly planned by Avventure Bellissime. From start to finish, they delivered a seamless, first-class experience that exceeded every expectation.\n\nWe started in Rome, where private transfers and exceptional guides brought the city’s ancient wonders to life, exploring the Catacombs, St. Clemente Church, the Colosseum, Ancient Rome, the Vatican Museums, Sistine Chapel, and St. Peter’s Basilica. From there, we traveled to Sorrento, with a fascinating stop and guided tour in Pompeii, followed by breathtaking boat tours to Capri, the Blue Grotto, and along the stunning Amalfi Coast, visiting Positano and Amalfi.\n\nNext was Florence, where we dove into Renaissance history with private tours of the Duomo, Accademia Gallery (Michelangelo’s David), the Uffizi, and the city’s many beautiful landmarks. We ventured out to Cinque Terre, visiting Manarola and Monterosso by boat, plus a stop in Pisa to see the iconic Leaning Tower. Another highlight was a scenic tour of Siena and San Gimignano, topped with a wine tasting and delicious lunch in Monteriggioni in Tuscany.\n\nOur final stop was Venice, where we enjoyed a private Grand Canal boat tour, explored the islands of Murano (with a glass-blowing demo) and Burano, and capped the trip with two wine tours in the Valpolicella region, tasting amazing Amarone wines.\n\nThroughout the trip, Avventure Bellissime arranged beautiful 4-star hotels with breakfast in each city, coordinated all private transfers (including high-speed train tickets and water taxis), and provided outstanding local guides. Most impressively, they stayed in touch with us daily through WhatsApp to make sure everything went smoothly and to offer assistance at any time.\n\nWe had one traveler in a wheelchair with a broken toe, and every single driver and guide was incredibly accommodating, adjusting tours and transportation with great care and kindness to meet our needs.\n\nAvventure Bellissime took all the stress out of planning and delivered a truly once-in-a-lifetime experience. We cannot recommend them highly enough to anyone considering travel in Italy. Every moment was perfectly curated, effortless, enriching, and unforgettable.','2025-06-22 12:20:30','Google','2025-12-15 19:03:20'),(258,279,'betsy ern','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108385197252712100706/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV362Zds5z3JJIP3MBGqcoXtnViDKx2u16dUHiDwIuUKd0RbdMO=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Our third trip with this wonderful group! From planning to follow-through, our agents made traveling abroad as stress-free as possible. They are always there to step in when needed and we so appreciate their expertise which makes touring so enjoyable!\nOur trip involved five people - my husband and me, our older son and our younger son with his wife. I couldn\'t have sorted out all the details without Nurila\'s help. The guides are always so knowledgeable and enjoyable - great storytellers! The hotels chosen were wonderful and travel between locations comfortable and professional. Loved our drivers too! Highly recommend this group and look forward to our next adventure with them. XOXOXO','2025-12-05 18:03:51','Google','2025-12-15 19:03:20'),(259,279,'Hemanta Sarkar','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106728407362193737110/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMQHoHonPLCqYjzORkmQmN2_6oACrrvHvMo78EfEc3iLrWjw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Thanks to Monica and Nurila for meticulously and expertly planning and organizing an excellent 11-night/12-day trip to Italy, covering Rome, Pompeii, Amalfi Coast (Positano), Florence, Cinque Terre and Venice. We immensely enjoyed our trip, and we will fondly cherish the memories of this trip for a long time to come.\nAll the assigned tour guides (Anna, Barbara, Francesca, Antonella, Ciro, Ernesto, Giovani and Cristina) were excellent. Particularly, we learned a lot about the history, culture and art of ancient Italy from Barbara, Francesca, Antonella and Cristina – our tour guides in Rome, Florence and Venice. Ciro, a third generation tour guide at Pompeii, expertly guided us through the ruins of Pompeii. There was a small misunderstanding about visiting Positano in the Amalfi Coast, but it was quickly resolved by the Avventure Team.\nAll our hotels were well chosen. Particularly, we will have a very fond memory of the Hotel Tirrenia in Sorrentino – the view from our hotel room balcony was so beautiful that we were thinking of extending our stay in there!\nWe extend our heartfelt thanks to everyone in Avventure Bellissime for making this trip memorable. We will definitely recommend them to all our friends and relatives.','2025-11-02 12:21:42','Google','2025-12-15 19:03:20'),(260,279,'Tom Helget','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106568064807189307631/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlOSDvGJf4QGW9jrcInu10i80o2Ppk40msjZW1ZOAonBcalA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Avventure Bellissime arranged two incredible private tours of Assisi and Siena for my wife and I.  Both of our guides, Claudia and Lisa, were wonderful! They were friendly, informative and very knowledgeable about their respective city.  Our tours were arranged based on our specific needs and Claudia and Lisa were willing to modify the tours based on our requests. Both cities are very unique and definitely worth seeing. When family and friends ask what we liked best about our time in Italy, we both respond our tours of Assisi and Siena.  If you plan to go, we highly recommend you contact Avventure Bellissime as you will have a terrific experience learning about any city they offer.','2025-10-07 15:21:39','Google','2025-12-15 19:03:20'),(261,280,'Eric Brodsky','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110524575805307646021/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPfOwnNwweTNqa-heVqo99yMM0fe1zVoczwTxYSo3N-aAl5Al7GA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Incredible escape from the normal tourist trap.\nWe were amazed by the tranquil setting and our peaceful stroll thru the meticulously cared for gardens.\nThere is a one of a kind hedge maze that I guarantee you’ll get lost in. Lots of neat stuff at the gift shop and even a small food truck! You’d be a fool not to check this place out!','2025-06-18 19:51:47','Google','2025-12-15 19:04:55'),(262,280,'Catherine Galasso','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108465245791999285706/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_6_YCZRalDVP8uJTnJkdSyjBxW_yfL3Uv-OHXp6kby-xg1RWq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Super awesome garden to explore. Especially the labyrinth and the island of rabbits. The whole place is well maintained and