n the high 20s so the shade of the trees was most welcome.   The boxwood maze was particularly interesting - at 400 years old it is one of the oldest in Europe and there was a tower in the centre so you could see your route out if you needed to.  There was an island for rabbits who looked to be enjoying the sun, safe from predators and some lovely water features as well as shaded walks.  We really should have visited the arboretum too but we decided to head back to Ferrara instead.','2024-10-05 08:51:36','Google','2025-12-15 19:04:55'),(266,281,'Vi Os','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104119851177285833159/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXPdyRv9mB_PA6pohg9PkEU9LILTGK7Wj73Y2_XkbPRt3QfVYzbg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'A nice small museum that feels quiet and peaceful. The exhibition is not large, but it is presented in an interesting and clear way, so it’s easy to walk through and learn something new. The atmosphere is calm, the space is clean, and the staff is polite. It’s a good place for a short visit if you want something simple, quiet, and informative.','2025-11-23 09:08:08','Google','2025-12-15 19:06:52'),(267,281,'Pandaz','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100303203045051136425/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhqPesSoPGarCTd4xafadloRd1ju1AAX8D8bxZX3cAUelAeQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'It\'s a very small museum but you\'ll find some incredible lace works.\nThe video on the ground floor before you go up to see the works is quite long but worth watching.\nSpacious locker room is available for you to store your belongings for comfortable time in the museum','2025-10-07 12:57:19','Google','2025-12-15 19:06:52'),(268,281,'Seokjin Ham','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100335057264723274172/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhtf6A7X2UDP--Xi1vhwXxfhLJk0GUh_pTYJvgqrBOTATbUg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',4,'Located in the Palazzo del Podestà of Torcello, the museum opened in 1981 and houses around 200 pieces of lacework dating from the 16th to the 20th century. It highlights the craftsmanship and artistic tradition of lace-making in Venice and its surrounding lagoon islands, particularly Burano, which is famed for its delicate lace. The museum is situated in the same building where the Burano Lace School operated from 1872 to 1970, training generations of artisans in this intricate craft. After extensive renovations, the museum was reopened in 2011 with updated exhibition spaces and a renewed focus on preserving and showcasing this unique element of Venetian cultural heritage.\n※ Included in the Venice Museum Pass.','2025-06-15 11:59:40','Google','2025-12-15 19:06:52'),(269,281,'hila','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114379598090924322233/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVnVrpex--yAImloT1AzEbPoDu9c-VrsnbMIe4dP_ub0Z5xsj5FQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',5,'This small museum illustrates the history of lace-making in Burano and features exhibitions of beautiful, intricate lacework. It’s included in the Venice Museum Pass and is a recommended stop if you\'re visiting the island.\nVisiting Burano itself is also highly recommended — it\'s like a smaller, more picturesque version of Venice, with far fewer crowds but all the charm.','2025-05-16 18:10:30','Google','2025-12-15 19:06:52'),(270,281,'Renato Camargo','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111942822060693359334/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiaX1F_6S03KK4c1RInwvHS82VTnHc67rYcsRLGW3fARUGyA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',3,'Not expensive, but not much to see. Beautiful work. If you are not a lace lover you may spend 10 to 15 minutes inside.','2025-10-13 07:58:57','Google','2025-12-15 19:06:52'),(271,282,'Ollie Fitton-Cook','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109201603382553758807/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFm66wehqblBxyWytwtERC76aEjSSUsun5m608Y_Tq7LXpWv-C=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'A fantastic museum on modern Italian history, I really learned a lot about how the country has changed and there were lessons to be learned for citizens of other nations. The museum is dual-language, Italian and English.','2025-11-03 15:54:22','Google','2025-12-15 19:08:47'),(272,282,'Stuart Morley','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114564713852410669668/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9csWUuxquxtBhFnRoaVBsBY9MOa1Tk6ak57Oads-uSqBUTcRL=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Superb museum. Didn’t know what to expect and was looking for something to do in Mestre. Very good museum and extremely well done with no expense spared. Nearly all is in Italian and English. Well worth a visit.','2025-09-17 11:14:15','Google','2025-12-15 19:08:47'),(273,282,'Meriliis Jõhve','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115096895596292961579/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGpkyAs5-BuBAPtx_ls0upvOaE46_9pc-FTs2O7tMSTvX5alH_=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'It was the best museum I have ever been! Very new and interesting. All the nowadays solutions can make history much easier to learn. Also, one of the goals was learn about local culture and as the rooms were very interactive I felt like some local gave me all the information. It felt very personal. Thank you for lovely staff who are working there and the people who designed this amazing museum! It really is the best and must visit if you are in Venice.','2025-10-11 08:16:54','Google','2025-12-15 19:08:47'),(274,282,'Robert Freeman','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103790735370237817964/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVA99DT_oY1WqYuEN_lGM9xpPCMNstDQeJ3q8D4dS4xApuvt480tg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',5,'Completely brilliant and amazing museum, exploring the last hundred years of life in Italy. Interactive, intriguing, informative and inspiring. We spent *six hours* exploring.','2024-09-29 17:43:44','Google','2025-12-15 19:08:47'),(275,282,'Pandaz','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100303203045051136425/reviews','ht