lly rolled her eyes at me. I liked the earrings, and the only reason I didn’t buy them was her attitude. If she wants to sell anything, she might want to learn to be polite to people – it’s the most basic thing to do.','2025-11-13 17:32:40','Google','2025-12-15 19:11:54'),(286,285,'Bob M','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111434108040052784561/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ-5I83H1ZcfYNdD1xBLCe0JSzMuU0R6ly15ZSk9YA3YfLw3Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'We stayed two nights and had a positive experience. We arrived by water taxi from the airport which pulled right up to a door at reception so no dragging or bags over Venice bridges!!!  Staff helped us schedule a departure taxi and even adjusted to boat/car alternative when weather didn’t allow boats outside of the canals on departure day.\n\nThe hotel is two buildings, the main building with reception and restaurants is a quirky gem, like being in palace. We were in the next door building which is less ornate. We had two rooms which were comfortable. We did not have water views from our rooms but common areas offered Grand Canal views. Keep in mind there are LOTS of stairs and no elevator. Staff did help with our bags but it still was 3.5 flights up steep stairs to our attic room.\n\nBreakfast was €18 and was a fairly standard European spread.\n\nThe real benefit was location. Located on a quiet street which ends at the hotel but is 1 minute away from many restaurants and shops.\n\nThe price was significant, service was very good and staff was helpful but keep in mind this is somewhat of a “rustic” luxury experience.','2025-10-07 11:43:12','Google','2025-12-15 19:13:20'),(287,285,'Panthera','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107765916672244007926/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXalzYcJUwyg1U9fTQwP3sHyPDbVVttUCQ7vr5aq67XSxOfEME=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Beautiful authentic Venetian hotel! Wonderfully renovated, with stunning common areas full of character. I highly recommend having dinner at the restaurant at least once (you can even dine on the balcony for two). The service is excellent, and there’s a great variety at breakfast. You can also arrive directly by water taxi, as the hotel is located on the canal.','2025-10-21 07:45:14','Google','2025-12-15 19:13:20'),(288,285,'Hamza Sawa','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109382327661646116232/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAYVpQW_qHhnEuIGvI-q-GgWkjoAZqUPMFB3LhFAYC6qa3u_n7=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Staying at this hotel was truly a unique experience. The building is very old and beautifully decorated, making you feel like you’ve stepped back into the medieval times, with all the charm and atmosphere of history surrounding you. The interiors are full of character, with antique details that create an unforgettable ambiance. Despite its historic style, everything was perfectly maintained, comfortable, and clean. The staff were warm and welcoming, and the service was excellent. From the atmosphere to the comfort, it’s easily one of the most memorable hotels I’ve ever stayed in, and I would highly recommend it to anyone visiting the area.','2025-08-21 13:54:52','Google','2025-12-15 19:13:20'),(289,285,'D Vetrano','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114104292615025408188/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnUUhYtAjoZXuS1pHQ8BH2Fs75A5MZpFU4hX0N8gR1vgHu0kc9=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Amazing. I have been coming to Venice for over 40 years and this Hotel is wonderful. Intimate, luxurious and well situated. The hotel maintains it\'s historically past while offering contemporary features such as a modern bathroom where the shower has been situated to provide a view of the grand canal. Service is helpful but not obsequeious. The view from the dining room windows is perfect. Working from my suite was luxurious. Gilded age like. I literally worked for 40 years to build my life to move from staying in hostels to here. I now can die well!','2025-09-12 21:45:46','Google','2025-12-15 19:13:20'),(290,285,'Corey Nierzwick','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112323415083991103224/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWR4bmiBeBIo9CWaR8eBwRw6lgWxLv77n9L0LpKs_tMKOhAx1z9=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'My stay here has left me pondering, for a week, on how to write a review. They deserve 5 stars across the board. Whether it was the ambiance of old Venice, the delightful, kind and helpful staff, or the central location … the stay is beyond describable and applicable words. As an individual who is planning to move to Padua next year, they were able to help guide me through learning new phrases and words in Italian, while being completely able to speak multiple languages. Even the staff with lesser English knowledge were able to communicate through humorous body language, creating an intimate and joyful conversation (I say this as someone who works with individuals who communicate with sign language and communication devices).\nI chose to explore rather than be sent to locations but, the staff were entirely capable of this gesture. An individual did direct me to a company who can help with visas, language lessons, work … etc and everything I will need.\nMy room was upgraded at no additional cost, my first night I wanted a drink after their bar closed and I was able to be accommodated due to the kind hearted staff who understood my jet lag.\nWhen my friends or family come to visit me, they will stay here, as there cannot be any place better.\nWith lifelong memories made, it was truly a privilege, joy and honor to have been a guest.','2025-08-27 19:46:33','Google','2025-12-15 19:13:20'),(291,286,'Blanca Gnefkow','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113340743139945485184/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5GPhH-FxKzJ-CsdUUEW6r1SRns6bmr25aNARmzFCTDEt0Bw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'My mom and I did a photoshoot in Venice this past summer with Pietro, and it ended up being one of the highlights of our trip. He made us feel comfortable right away and walked us through beautiful bridges and quiet corners of the city we would’ve never found on our own. His attention to detail is incredible the notices angles, lighting, and small moments that make the pictures feel so natural and alive.\n\nThe final photos were stunning and captured the bond between my mom and me perfectly. It’s an experience we’ll always treasure, and I highly recommend booking with Pietro if you want meaningful, timeless photos in Venice.','2025-12-02 00:06:27','Google','2025-12-15 19:14:32'),(292,286,'Alex Pelaez','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115138027027964011697/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAlAR6I5kyp7guS1pMvVRf_zgcGC_6Leq5eXiqTJtPGQ6Hxag=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'I am so glad that Sarah, my wife and I had a the opportunity to shoot with Pietro.  He was fantastic and extremely knowledgeable of his trade and of beloved Venice.  Highly recommend him to you for your photo needs in Venice.','2025-11-13 01:28:59','Google','2025-12-15 19:14:32'),(293,286,'Valeria Morell','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100561007450388413660/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXASIAilfFKakrb5xeyiGipBwS7kVthqRe225QU-GreMrSnK9Gg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'We booked Pietro for our trip to Italy and it was the best decision we could’ve made. Pietro is an amazing and sweet photographer, and served to us also as friend and tour guide. We had an excellent time, got amazing recommendations for dinner, gelato, and drinks, and beautiful photos which we started to receive the day after and got all our pictures before we were even back home. Trust me you won’t regret booking your photo shoot!','2025-03-22 17:37:56','Google','2025-12-15 19:14:32'),(294,286,'Mary Dustan','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107807042050442727735/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7xBsA-HYyhT02SLRchIVCdzIAn4kltgDOku0syHaVFTejxA=s128-c0x0000