.com/maps/contrib/104565797983071896792/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1ese4PVTr33Y1azAfLipDavr-qwLaz5gyhDotI7tZPYPvi8Mz=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Nice folk music and dancing show in the basement of the Vienna city hall.  There is no elevator so you must navigate two flog HR a of stairs to enjoy the venue.','2024-07-16 18:01:57','Google','2025-12-15 19:29:17'),(338,295,'Robyn Becker','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109108199507250802298/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIc9PpjUUSYAQetp_sSj5G68H_Rtj4D3Xd1Hj_18YHV8lxoeg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',4,'This dinner and show is perfect for people travelling on a budget.  You get a lovely 3 course meal of traditional Viennese flavours and a glimpse of Viennese Opera and dance.   This is one of the cheaper dinner and concert shows and you get what you pay for.  All other shows are double the price.  The only disappointment was that the website said it included many songs from the Sound of Music which would have been an absolute highlight and instead there was only one song.   The dessert could have been served a little better - certainly not photo worthy and was a little dry.  Just a warning, there are other dinner venues within this building and you are caught right at the entrance to pay €3 to hang your coat.  There are coat racks at no charge in the dinner theatre so no need to pay.     We enjoyed the experience for what we paid.  The singers and musicians were very talented.','2022-04-24 08:20:18','Google','2025-12-15 19:29:17'),(339,295,'Aaron H','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104328463148261725182/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJvbiTm83IbuTS97YCwlwjY829I7OVvsQMss64hxxM5L_aJ0wcxA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',2,'This review is divided into two parts: 1. The performance, and 2. The food. Overall, not worth the money because of the terrible food.\n1. The performance is very good and entertaining. The show is excerpts from operettas. The musicians are wonderful and the singers and dancers are very talented. They give you a good show.\n2. The food and service are one to two stars, at best. Not good Austrian food at all. The starter a variety of aufstritch, one of which had an unauthentic tortilla chip. The main consisted of an overcooked, tough beef roll. The dessert kaiserschmarn arrived cold and rubbery (should be warm, light and fluffy).  Sad, sad food served by only two waiters.','2023-09-24 16:09:30','Google','2025-12-15 19:29:17'),(340,295,'Elaine P','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117393932895273902071/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK7S3NW61Q-MSDXGVtKVjy3LGhOVdovNtEdii2V1ngvnfCaaA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',2,'Very disappointing! The venue setting was very nice, but the rest of the evening was a let down. Whilst the food was ok, the portion sizes were not overly generous. The drinks were ridiculously expensive. We were charged 21 Euros for 2 SMALL beers and a bottle of mineral water. The entertainment was mediocre at best and more could have been done to include International guests. Not recommended.','2019-09-14 16:41:45','Google','2025-12-15 19:29:17'),(341,296,'Hungry In Seychelles','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110892487440986853100/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV16MOl4JDDb5z1pKxfpkzSkPR2Rzba2Gq79NHRMOMK1c4eZznN=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Went to see Gustav Klimt on exhibition and it was a wonderful experience to see his work alongside Monet, Van Gogh and Egon Schiele. The palace is easy to navigate and the exhibition was over 3 floors. I visited late 5pm before closing and it was not crowded. I got to see all the works up close and truly appreciate the details. Staff are very vigilant and protect the work from people standing too close, its also important to check sinage as its not permitted to take photos of all the work. I had a wonderful time exploring the grounds before sunset. Found bamboo in the botanical gardens. It was not so lush as we are at the end of autumn, but it is a marvellous palace nevertheless.  There is a cafe with very attentive and kind staff, great coffee. We also were very lucky the xmas markets were on at the time. Some beautiful stalls with great artisanal items!','2025-11-24 06:07:14','Google','2025-12-15 19:30:24'),(342,296,'Dave Trendell','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114841652793446016018/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJNgXUV7UsdLkJa9ulLCcL7CrdlvV_4rcvtpCMPorFAdswGHD2=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Visually stunning place and a great Christmas market. Sadly didn\'t get a chance to go in as it was fully booked but the gardens were really lovely to walk around. Hopefully the next time we are in Vienna we can visit again.','2025-12-05 20:07:46','Google','2025-12-15 19:30:24'),(343,296,'Yağmur Bayındır','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109684459653190364938/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjybId7HaA2nqzNE1A8BJGnVSkEQ7ObPnM2QcMO0S_BAlF9LpQog=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'This is a must see place if you visit Vienna. Many pieces of famous painters, and beautifully designed rooms with a baroque architecture.\nMy visit was in November which was also coincided with the Chrismast Market in front if the palace, very nice  atmosphere. A huge garden which Im sure more beautiful in spring and summer.','2025-11-29 11:39:37','Google','2025-12-15 19:30:24'),(344,296,'Seda ORAL','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101255983604732349375/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKUfLrKa6fjOIZzca-Fx_FoTTxxh1vjZs_Ic0N2AAKRUor8cA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'It consists of two parts, Up and Down. It\'s an incredible experience. After visiting this place, you feel like you have taken a few hours of art history lessons. A place to never be missed when you arrive in Vienna','2025-11-25 19:47:53','Google','2025-12-15 19:30:24'),(345,296,'Yoana Mileva','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110115758345012231587/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXtgu2ad9areWJ8ExgBjoVvDC88TgpPYhT35_SSPqPZxGDZ0fQl=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'It was nice to visit this palace. In winter time it\'s not so lovely because of the gardens. There was a little Christmas Bazar where you can enjoy some wine and sweets. There was huge donuts and some traditional foods.','2025-11-24 19:16:46','Google','2025-12-15 19:30:24'),(346,297,'Lucian Marin','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115456628886222260247/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZLa3fJWwUUQDNoRz97lgnXTAn9l2mZjW5QVJQspgRkSkzB8hO=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'The Imperial Crypt lies beneath the Capuchin Church, and it\'s easy to miss if you just walk around. It\'s quite astonishing when you think that so many of the Habsburg line were buried here: 150 royals, including 12 emperors and 19 empresses/queens, from 1633 to the present day. There\'s written information at each tomb about their life and death. A fantastic read!\n\nOne of the most impressive tombs I found to be was Maria Theresa\'s. It\'s literally fills up an entire room on its own, while lying at her feet is her son, Joseph II, with a plain coffin. You can also find here the tomb of Emperor Franz Joseph I, the last emperor buried here, Empress Sisi and Crown Prince Rudolf.\n\nThe visit to the crypts is definitely worth it\'s price. You can easily spend up to 1.5 hours here. Bring your jacket, since it gets cold!','2025-12-04 13:21:53','Google','2025-12-15 19:31:47'),(347,297,'LemLem Oliveira','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102543349734334263563/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXahyFsuGPc9zNJ2Wo-XU5dXOYE4yDlRL3dJWhq0OZBNGNUIWJU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Wow - didn’t think a “museum” of sarcophaguses would be so interesting! Even my kid found it fascinating! Some of the sarcophaguses are so detailed and although most of them are eerie, it’s also very interesting to see how they were customized for that Individual (royal). Definitely worth a visit!','2025-10-02 21:51:06','Google','2025-12-15 19:31:47'),(348,297,'Ali k','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103571875734487679733/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-5fTkSMHRWHblplAZRWBACEVMHL3NLdOthx74RNQ_SjzKNKQq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',4,'I arrived in Vienna on a Saturday morning. After settling into my hotel, I decided to go for a stroll around the neighborhood and find some local lunch. During this walk, I stumbled upon a completely unexpected place: the Capuchin Church. It immediately reminded me of a school case study I had done on the Habsburg dynasty, and I decided to make a detour to see it up close.\nAfter making a small donation and lighting some candles, I found my way to the basement. I was excited to see the Imperial Crypt—the final resting place for generations of Austrian royalty. It was an eerie, quiet place; the air was cool and heavy with the weight of history. It truly felt like I had traveled back in time.\nThe crypt itself was a chillingly elegant gallery of eternal slumber. Each tomb, a silent monolith of power and artistry, was a testament to the lives they once lived and the empires they ruled. The craftsmanship on each crypt was incredibly detailed and breathtaking. As I walked among the elaborate sarcophagi, I was struck by the thought that these royal figures have been resting in these sealed tombs for so many years. The feeling of wandering among them, a lone intruder in their silent court, was both thrilling and profound.\nIt was a fascinating and slightly spooky experience, well worth skipping lunch for. And no, I didn\'t lose my appetite, though.','2025-09-02 17:55:49','Google','2025-12-15 19:31:47'),(349,297,'E Grove','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104500434139203224140/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBhOvyK0ptERQ20tW7de-5lbKDQR1DS2MyybhiOmfnt7bqD8cM5A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'The tour is worth the price. It\'s very quiet and I 