ps://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117169716056585365240/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDy7Mo63YazKJ1QebO5uwPLHIa-5JUXP57Lj3vi744b2Zi6K0i=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'I went with my parents — one of the coolest activities you can do in Amsterdam! 🙌🏻🙌🏻\nIt’s basically an interactive light and laser show, accompanied by amazing sound and music.\nThe experience is set up across several rooms, and you move from one to the next without knowing what to expect. Each space is a surprise — and every one is unique, fun, and super immersive. I won’t go into too much detail so it stays a surprise for you!\nIf you’ve got an hour or an hour and a half of free time, definitely check it out.\nIt’s great for kids, adults, and even older visitors. Just a heads-up: it’s not recommended for people with epilepsy, as the lights and effects could trigger seizures.\n\nWill go again, once I come back in Ams💙','2025-10-21 09:00:27','Google','2025-12-15 19:42:16'),(386,305,'Jun Herrera','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112138508941599176998/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-fdsj1Rv8W0hjFF1_sE6w4nvHe7vaigYN5sHSfP7eJlQwTMsa=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',4,'This cruise will get you around Amsterdam City. The boat captain will give you a glimpse of Amsterdam buildings and histories. It\'s a smooth sailing along the canal and open bay. Great ride.','2025-05-30 23:29:07','Google','2025-12-15 19:43:54'),(387,305,'VENKATESH PRABHU L','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117977748542127053861/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXK0lu0aXsgABVDfMj1QBUo_xA7wYEsXp4vUnl_feC0PSpou3Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'For any first time visitor to Amsterdam, a cruise on Amsterdam\'s canals is a must. By opting for it early in your trip, you stand to get a broad idea about city and the attractions it holds for you.','2025-08-11 04:52:25','Google','2025-12-15 19:43:54'),(388,305,'Krys K','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110392396542607213431/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwHSEpo_dJc9z9BAeeTTH3LUp5YgJPp5Y-Ll8X4fcnhR-3LY1D9A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Pleasant cruise on the canal with very little wait time. Staff is excellent. The boats are well kept up so you can enjoy the view from the large windows.','2025-01-03 12:29:45','Google','2025-12-15 19:43:54'),(389,305,'KN IWN','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113234314517691749806/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQWVPNtPSSNVBgnaEUzt1ume-k7USnZ0VOVElq2x0L7x2XDHji=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'When you are tired from walking around Amsterdam then why not just take a boat tour. This tour is quite nice as they have so many languages to choose from and we were quite surprised that there is Thai language too.\n\nOur boat has the glass roof which is quite nice when it’s cold outside. The window can be open if you feel too warm. To be honest, I would recommend to go with open air boat if it’s nice weather and not too cold.\n\nThe audio guide will explain you each highlight spot which is quite good + on the table is the map so you know where is it located or at least you know where you are.\n\nAt some point, it could become boring as you just sit inside the boat. Anyway, our boat rider is quite funny and sarcastic which make us don’t feel so sleepy.','2024-10-28 16:36:03','Google','2025-12-15 19:43:54'),(390,305,'Prabu M','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115122743546895562193/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYaMtkh480dZJQ3Sq6N5EZ6J1Tp99C0yTyoTtkGI8UWE7sPTHU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'The canal boat tour in Amsterdam is an absolute must-do, even in winter, thanks to the covered and heated boats. The one-hour ride offers breathtaking views of the city’s iconic canals, charming bridges, and historic architecture. As you glide through the waterways, you’ll also get to listen to fascinating stories about Amsterdam’s history. It’s a relaxing and scenic experience perfect for families and a great way to see the city from a unique perspective.','2024-12-23 20:32:16','Google','2025-12-15 19:43:54'),(391,306,'Jatin Khodiar','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108190729923183217438/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5Q5poJGI7hKQylWZldUOBvUr0Gpu_bWr1yzSfSeYqbvXoKgcl=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Had a great time at Amsterdam Dungeons! The whole experience was fun, interactive, and really well put together. I got picked to play the witch at the end and was chosen for another scene too, which made it even more memorable. The actors were brilliant, and the price felt fair for what you get. Definitely recommend it if you\'re in Amsterdam!','2025-07-22 18:27:56','Google','2025-12-15 19:45:35'),(392,306,'Kieran','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112724221494686846483/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVi7KvfSTcVIBzEdiFzaBm-pyd0JWjw1DOTGma1cUXPRLvplBTv=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'A really fun experience, all the live actors were fantastic and fitted there roles well. Really good value for the price would definitely recommend a visit. My only complaint would be it did feel the group was too big and not enough sits for a few of the acts felt cramped in places.','2025-11-15 12:09:44','Google','2025-12-15 19:45:35'),(393,306,'Faith Rohani','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112627499636428343452/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXZfDZjyXy3o-qf7ufvTtO-MNPwy1Cg47Mja3pleMAuBpJ4P5JUA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Information before the fun stuff, the address given takes you to a door that then tells you to go around the building a bit more and yes. For us, we got sent to a random bar, and then we had to refind the address and use that lol.\n\nNo photos allowed during the tour, but it was good, you get truly engulfed into the stories.\n\nOh this was nice, informational, fun, interactive, funny and scary (if you get spooked easily) they pick people within the small groups to have you act out stuff, and there\'s signs and such for the chosen ones to do to make the storyline better. The actors were amazing, the group i had within it was fun, and i was chosen by my cousin as a woman who was accused to witchcraft, and needed to be burned at the stake. There were signs and such to tell me to scream and act like i was being burned alive to make the story more alive. Afterwards, i got a little fun paper, and the actor told me i did amazing and to go ahead and rejoin the group. Anywayz overall, great experience.','2025-06-24 20:53:08','Google','2025-12-15 19:45:35'),(394,306,'Nirvesh Seedeehul','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106178666719705793035/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUog_b2hrZ4CIrodXgEquC_SqQtutrBl-0yFX0GsmI7MU69uiX=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Amazing experience. You can tell the actors r very passionate about what they\'re doing and overall the experience was really fun. My fav part has to be at the last story, won\'t spoil but the way it was, was so realistic you\'d think u were actually in a horror movie','2025-10-01 05:41:30','Google','2025-12-15 19:45:35'),(395,306,'Eman AlGhamdi','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105137132636310809354/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhfVoTC59PFUSCVOGrsGwis4BtQLEE7tM9ua40xawxCvIzQQ7K=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'We had such an amazing time at Dungeon Amsterdam! The whole experience was a perfect mix of scary, funny, and surprising. We got genuinely spooked at times, laughed a ton, and were totally amazed by the actors and the atmosphere. The storytelling, sets, and jump scares were all so well done. Highly recommend if you’re looking for something fun and different to do in Amsterdam!','2025-11-22 07:34:04','Google','2025-12-15 19:45:35'),(396,307,'Ahab','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117086963362013417751/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIzSXI0WR2h8lxsZQJhyK77xyR7M2l12_M-43JNtZVleRjlGJM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'My visit to the Royal Palace in Amsterdam was a truly special experience! The palace is stunning inside and reflects history and elegance in every corner. The interior design is magnificent, and the information provided during the tour was both useful and fascinating. I highly recommend visiting it to discover a beautiful part of Dutch history.','2025-10-25 09:01:22','Google','2025-12-15 19:47:13'),(397,307,'Francesco Cavina','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114006832722125964157/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2K4r5w9us6tcrD9MMIUg81j9V433s4OY2i2BnvHgoVzJzcw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Great experience! The audio tour is great, good timing and flexible. You can go around the halls you want and click on the corresponding tracks in the device you’re given (for free) at the entrance. Many languages included, with exhaustive explanations.\nReally like the aesthetic and architecture of the palace. Rooms are really cool and there is very interesting history behind it all. Definitely recommend having a visit!','2025-09-09 12:27:55','Google','2025-12-15 19:47:13'),(398,307,'Odette Houston','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107624049401009329202/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocISo7KZ-IA1G_BcoZnGEKKxxfZlFJuhE9kbsayUcX0TyiXGrQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Beautiful art! Astounding craftsmanship! Overall wonderful experience except for demonstrations having sprayed red paint on the outside windows and walls. We thought our tour was canceled but we entered through another entrance on the other side.','2025-10-15 06:42:30','Google','2025-12-15 19:47:13'),(399,307,'Liz 410','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114730365241794786543/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCOmRvqdUsiNT1sgGtZc7QLh28tIQyaUQ5WjuhdOoUjdWOBZLVJQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'I took a private tour through Viator of the palace.\n\nThe sculptures are among the best in the world.  The symbolism in each piece is astounding.\n\nThe rooms are beautiful, and every step you take is heavy with history.','2025-10-17 11:12:18','Google','2025-12-15 19:47:13'),(400,307,'Ji Ji','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113397264114916877573/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLMCItcfkV-piR8ZcmlBJmd0uY2jcaokGxvfsBuAvytEghKGg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'The Palace does not look interesting from the outside, but it is such a gem on the inside. There is an audioguide offered, and you can choose the longer or shorter version to listen to, which I think is very convenient (I would suggest the longer version as this place is worth the time). There may be a group of students or tourists getting in at the same time as you are, so make sure to set aside some time for the possibility of waiting in a queue for the wardrobe.','2025-11-17 14:42:25','Google','2025-12-15 19:47:13'),(401,308,'Linda Bailey','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103038778061184387285/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV13-ZLd5E8gbX7oVINRLkobXoW7aOrzbAdXFra4V8v2e0Q96I=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'We thought we would quickly visit the zoo as it was included with the ticket to Micropia. t was not a quick visit because the animals gave us 2 great shows:\n\nThe otter show: squeezing and crying made us go to the otter pool. There we found the otters all crying out plaintively for their lunch. They were making quite the racket and were so cute! The zookeeper came around 3:00 pm and fed each one a fish and it was amusing as they ate! What a lovely show!\n\nThen jaguars (one melanistic-black) were cavorting around their enclosure, licking each other and chasing each other. It was a great show of feline affection.\n\nUnfortunately we did not a lot enough time for the zoo. The animals looked so well cared for and it is heartwarming to see a varied group of humans, all enjoying the antics of the animals.','2025-12-03 06:08:50','Google','2025-12-15 19:48:57'),(402,308,'Mohammad Homsi','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109919088166368454317/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeKMbKqX4VHScYNrYB0QNly0CAG_21HT7BpQHOGn-Txs9v4Zw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'We had such a wonderful time at this zoo! 🐒🦁 From the moment we arrived, everything was well-organized and easy to navigate. The variety of animals was impressive — we saw everything from playful monkeys to majestic lions, and even some adorable penguins. The enclosures were clean and spacious, and it was clear the animals are well cared for.\n\nThe staff were friendly and happy to answer questions, and there were plenty of spots to rest, grab a snack, or take great photos. It’s a perfect place for families, couples, or anyone who loves animals. We left with big smiles and some great memories.','2025-08-12 12:11:01','Google','2025-12-15 19:48:57'),(403,308,'Adnan Kh','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108041564055843630068/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX7yQjMdeA5HyIdB-UKeEdYDCZsaMN1CB8FXlFiw6nLMD7lpFIf=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'ARTIS Zoo is a hidden gem in the heart of Amsterdam! It’s beautifully laid out, with a great mix of animals, botanical gardens, and historical architecture. The enclosures are well-maintained, and the animals seem well cared for. I especially enjoyed spending quality family time here with my grandchildren — there was something magical for all ages. Highlights include the aquarium, planetarium, and butterfly pavilion. The peaceful atmosphere and lush greenery make it feel more like a park than a typical zoo. A perfect spot for a relaxing, educational day out. Definitely worth a visit','2025-09-14 09:16:44','Google','2025-12-15 19:48:57'),(404,308,'Tabatha O','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109025491508394432587/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiqptyhyT7BAOo4in9OJttMQpvUjZYPdVfjPpAFWZrKZPLYzE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'I’ve been to dozens of zoos across the US and Europe and this is one of the most beautiful. Lovely enclosures and the pathways and buildings are lovely as well. The animals seemed quite lively compared to other zoos as well.','2025-11-17 07:21:55','Google','2025-12-15 19:48:57'),(405,308,'Maria Mane','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100241040576872412866/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLcYbhhR8xY9HOUo4rim440eZBKzFsgM2u18JurYCS7aG_F8A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'A large zoo with a wide variety of animals and plenty to see and explore! The planetarium was a fun bonus and added something unique to the visit. There are vegan food options available, though a bit on the pricey side.\n\nSome enclosures could definitely be improved, especially for the crocodiles, who seemed to have very limited space.\n\nOverall, it was a fun and enjoyable day. Great for visiting with friends or family.','2025-07-23 15:47:42','Google','2025-12-15 19:48:57');
